Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.72,0:01:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他说4分钟 多一秒少一秒都不行\NHe said four minutes precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.56,0:02:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 不\NNon, non, non.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,再拿两个来 快点\NQuickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.48,0:02:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这次的鸡蛋应该很完美了吧\NTwo perfect eggs this time, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.92,0:02:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,也许吧\NMaybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.96,0:02:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,看来是鸡的错\NI blame the chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:02:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,母鸡下蛋时候没有算好尺寸\NWhy do hens lay eggs of different sizes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.24,0:02:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是你的错\NIt's not you, mon ami.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这两个鸡蛋很完美\NThese are two perfectly good oeufs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.28,0:02:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛先生\NMr. Poirot...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,三名神职人员都带来了\NI've got three religions bent on riot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.28,0:03:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,您准备好大显身手的话\NIf you're going to perform one of your miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是时候了\Nthe time is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,鸡蛋你留着吃 我们走\NHave the eggs. Allons-y!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛\NPoirot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.96,0:03:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 你踩到了\NSorry for the, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.96,0:03:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,问题并不在于\NIt is not the, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.12,0:03:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,而是在于一种不平衡感\NIt is the imbalance of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.64,0:03:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,好多了\NThat's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.92,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,借过 让我们过去\NExcuse me. Coming through.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.96,0:03:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,请让一让\NMake way, please. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.80,0:03:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,把三名嫌疑犯都带上来\NPlease call for the accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,拉比\NThe rabbi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.80,0:03:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,神父\Nthe priest...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.16,0:03:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,伊玛目\Nand the imam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,是不是很像以前的一个笑话\NIt is like the old joke, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,拉比 神父 伊玛目\NThe rabbi, the priest, and the imam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,请见谅 我是比利时人\NForgive me, I am Belgian.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.32,0:04:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,那开始吧\NSo, let us begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就在这里的圣墓大教堂里面\NIn the Church of the Holy Sepulchre above us...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的三位代表\Nthree representatives meet under the supervision...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.00,0:04:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,在总督察的监督下进行了会面\Nof the Chief Inspector of Police
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.68,0:04:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,为了商讨轮流使用集市的时间表\Nto discuss a divided timetable for market use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.84,0:04:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,紧张的会面结束一小时后\NOne hour after this tense meeting...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,教堂里一件价值连城的文物被偷了\Na priceless relic is found to be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,有人说 小偷就在 这三个人之中\NIt is said, one of these three men has stolen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.92,0:04:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,警方至今未能找到任何证据\NThe police find no pieces of evidence at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,而我找到了一个\NI find one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.88,0:04:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,证据就在教堂内保存完好的壁画上\NOn the meticulously well-kept wall of a fresco...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一道细微的裂痕 应该是一个\Na single crack from an indelicate climb...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,穿着硬底鞋或者靴子的人 在笨手笨脚攀爬时留下\Nwith a hard-soled shoe or perhaps a boot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.56,0:05:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那么 在场的各位一定会问\NSo, ladies and gentlemen, we must ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.40,0:05:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,谁是此案中最大的受益者呢\Nwho stands to benefit from the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.24,0:05:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的三位神职人员 生活简朴\NOur three holy men live humbly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.24,0:05:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他们买不起这么高档的鞋子\NThey're thin-soled shoes poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.56,0:05:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,突如其来的金银财宝\NSudden riches and rubies would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.56,0:05:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,对他们来说太显眼了 不是吗 他们根本无福消受\Ntoo conspicuous, yes, to enjoy. They do not gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.60,0:05:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,此时我需要一个警卫去守住南门\NAt this point, we need an armed guard at the south gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.96,0:05:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,所以唯一\NNo, the only one...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,能在这次偷盗事件中 以及事件所产生的骚乱中获益的人\Nwho benefits from the theft and the unrest it causes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.44,0:05:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我今早已经派人搜过他的办公室了\Nis a man whose office I had searched this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我正在等早餐\Nas I waited, I have to tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.64,0:05:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,说实话 我对那顿早餐很失望\Nrather disappointedly upon my breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,是鸡蛋的问题 我就不细说了\NDifficulty with eggs. You don't need to know this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.08,0:05:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,此人拿着丰厚的薪水 来维持耶路撒冷的秩序\NA man who is paid lavishly to keep order in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.72,0:05:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的那个人\NI mean, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.32,0:05:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我们的总督察\Nthe Chief Inspector of the Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.40,0:05:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,当他听到周围的民众\NA man who does not wish to lose a well-paid post...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,都嚷嚷着要自治\Nwhen there is discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.60,0:06:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他就害怕自己会失去这份高薪职位\Namong the local peoples of self-governance...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这个人穿得起靴子 而且我相信\Nwho does wear boots, and who, I believe, now does regret...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他现在一定很后悔 请我来调查这起案件\Ninviting me to consult on this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.48,0:06:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你竟敢这么污蔑我\NHow dare you accuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,麻烦你警官\NPlease, Sergeant...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.64,0:06:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,按照我说的搜过他的办公室了吗\Ndid you search the office as I asked?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.80,0:06:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 先生\NUh, yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.12,0:06:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,有找到我和你说的那样东西吗\NAnd did you find what I said you might?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.76,0:06:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 先生 就是您所说的那个\NUh, yes, sir. Just as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.12,0:06:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NMerci.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,站住\NHalt!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.52,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,需要你送过去\NYou need to deliver that, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,明早第一批就送过去\NIt should be through first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 先生\NVery good, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.36,0:07:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,您的行李都装好了 先生\NLuggage is on board, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,很荣幸能送您上船\NI won the right to escort you to your boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.28,0:07:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,去伊斯坦布尔吗\NTo Stamboul, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,然后直接回伦敦吗\NWill you be back to London straight off?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.84,0:07:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我有点儿累了 所以想给自己放一个长假\NI am tired, and I have earned myself a little holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,想去看看画展\NI want to look at paintings
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.28,0:07:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,反正有的是时间\Nand have too much time on my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.36,0:07:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直盯着我看 有什么事么\NYou are staring. Does it stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.04,0:07:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是\NIt's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,您怎么知道是他干的\NHow did you know it was him, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.80,0:07:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,就凭墙上的那条细缝吗\NFrom just a tiny crack on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.96,0:07:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我这人有一个天赋\NI have the advantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.64,0:07:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我的眼里只容得下真实的世界\NI can only see the world as it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.72,0:07:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是很小的瑕疵都会变得特别显眼\NAnd when it is not, the imperfection stands out...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.72,0:07:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,就像脸上的鼻子那样\Nlike the nose in the middle of a face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.84,0:08:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这会让生活变得无法忍受\NIt makes most of life unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.52,0:08:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但在办案的时候倒是非常有帮助\NBut it is useful in the detection of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,感觉您能看穿他们的心思\NBut it's as though you see into their hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.40,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,探知他们的本性\Nand divine their true natures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.88,0:08:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不管人们说了什么\NAnd whatever people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.32,0:08:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,要么是对的 要么是错的\Nthere is right, there is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.40,0:08:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,没有灰色地带\NThere is nothing in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.92,0:08:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,就送到这儿吧\NWe must part here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.40,0:08:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不 先生 我得送你上船\NOh, no, sir, I'm to escort you on the ferry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.88,0:08:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,再见了上尉\NAu revoir, mon capitaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.32,0:08:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可能不会再见了\NWe must never meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.20,0:08:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,能不能麻烦你把领带摆正一点\NCould you straighten your tie, please? Just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 很完美\NYes. That is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.60,0:08:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,请所有乘客上船\NFinal passengers, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.68,0:08:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起\NOh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.84,0:08:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,很快就修好了\NWill be fixed soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,能及时修好吗\NBut, will it be fixed in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.60,0:08:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在想办法\NWe are working!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.76,0:08:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我要去伊斯坦布尔转火车\NI have a connection in Stamboul.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:08:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,明天7点发车\NLeaves tomorrow at seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.44,0:08:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,有一个重病患者还在伦敦等着我\NThere's a very ill patient waiting for me in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.40,0:08:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我是名医生\NI am a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.44,0:08:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,医生\NDoctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我是一名医生\NI am a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.28,0:09:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我居然用英文冲着你们喊\NI am shouting at you in English,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,嗓门那么大 还说的那么慢\Nand now I'm doing it louder and slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.88,0:09:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我真蠢 请见谅\NVery silly, forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.88,0:09:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,要帮忙吗 让我来吧\NMay I help? Let me help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.08,0:09:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我认得你的胡子\NI know your mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.48,0:09:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我在报纸上见过\NFrom the papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你是名侦探 赫拉克勒斯·波洛\NYou're the detective, Hercules Poirot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.28,0:09:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫赫尔克里·波洛 你说的那位是杀死狮子的大力神\NHercule Poirot. I do not slay the lions. Mademoiselle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,名字我可能记错了\NMary Debenham, monsieur.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.40,0:09:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但脸不会错\NI'll forget a name but never a face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.32,0:09:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,至少你的脸我不会记错\NNot yours, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.48,0:09:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你是从巴格达来的吗\NYou come from Baghdad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,看来那些传闻是真的 什么都瞒不过您的眼睛\NIt's true. No detail escapes his notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.84,0:09:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,票上写着呢\NYour ticket. Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.40,0:09:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我还想问您在那儿当家庭教师\NI might also ask you if you enjoyed your time there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.68,0:09:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,还算愉快吧\Nas a governess?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.76,0:09:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,您袖口上的粉笔灰还有您的地理读物\NThe chalk on your sleeve and the geography primer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.00,0:09:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不是家庭教师就是地图测绘员 我猜了一个\NA governess or a cartographer. I made my gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我一般喜欢从地理教起\NI always begin them with geography...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,然后逼着学生们把全世界都装到脑子里去\Nand monster them till they have the world down cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.76,0:10:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,生活中可以迷失方向\NThey may get lost in life...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但不知道自己在哪儿可不行\Nbut I'll be damned if they don't know where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,障碍清除了 时间刚刚好\NWell, our chains are free. Right on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.52,0:10:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在海上的感觉真是自由啊\NI feel so free out here on the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.28,0:10:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜我没有这个心情\NI wish I could enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.56,0:10:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们应该退出 玛丽\NWe should be out of this, Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.00,0:10:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 现在不行\NNot now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,等一切都结束了\NWhen it's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.48,0:10:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,事成之后\NWhen it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就没有人能阻碍我们了\NThen, nothing can touch us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我的假期即将从这儿开启\NAh, my holiday begins here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.48,0:11:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我能从这些朴实的烤饼里 窥探到这座城市的灵魂\NI can see the soul of the city in these humble breads.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.32,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这个世界不断地走向毁灭 而在这儿\NThe world insists on destruction, yet here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,每天都有新鲜出炉的大师之作\Nmasterpieces are baked to order every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.80,0:11:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛先生\NMonsieur Poirot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,穆罕默德\NMohammed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,穆罕默德 我的朋友\NMohammed, my friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.40,0:11:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是个艺术家\Nyou are an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我的朋友\NAh! My friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.32,0:11:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.96,0:11:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 过来\NHere. Come, come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.84,0:11:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,别介意 我们只想\NDon't mind us, we're just looking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.12,0:11:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,找个地方谈点私事\Nfor a place to have a private argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.60,0:11:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,大概也就二十来分钟吧\NIt should take some 20 minutes or so...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.28,0:11:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,等我们谈妥了\Nat which point we will both
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,或者至少我满意了就行\Ncome to an agreement, or at least I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.96,0:11:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 布克先生 - 波洛\NMonsieur Bouc!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.64,0:11:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,居然在厨房里见到你\NPoirot! In the kitchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.04,0:11:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 这位先生嗅探\NWell, of course, this man will sniff out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.08,0:12:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,美味酥饼的速度\Na perfect pastry faster than he catches...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.64,0:12:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,比他抓珠宝大盗的速度更快\Na jewel thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.80,0:12:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我亲爱的朋友\NMon ami!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在不是警探了\NNow, I am no longer a policeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.92,0:12:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你再犯事的话可没人捞你出来\NI cannot bail you out when this goes badly, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,这位是我的老朋友 受人敬仰的波洛\NThis is my dear, old friend, the esteemed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.48,0:12:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他出名前我们就认识了 而这位是\NPoirot, who I knew before the esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.24,0:12:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛 这位是\NHercule Poirot, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.64,0:12:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 一个妓女 - 是的\NA prostitute. She is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.80,0:12:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,说的对 布克 你从没提过你有这么有名的朋友\NI am. Bouc, you did not tell me you had famous friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.52,0:12:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我们之所以是朋友\NWe're friends because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.60,0:12:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,就是因为我从不过问他案子上的事\NI'm the only person who never asks him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.68,0:12:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我根本就不在乎\Nany questions about his cases, because I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.52,0:12:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,而他也从不嫌弃我人品差\NAnd he never judges me for being a terrible person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.32,0:12:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,确实很差\NIndeed you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.44,0:12:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,女士 布克 一起喝一杯如何\NMadame, Bouc, please join me for a drink, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.24,0:12:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我只能陪你一小时\NYou only have me for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.80,0:12:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我还要赶7点的东方快车\NI ride on the Orient Express at seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.76,0:12:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我是他们公司的董事\Nofficial director business.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.60,0:12:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我叔叔出高薪聘请我\NUncle pays me absurdly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,让我在他豪华的列车上工作\Nto stay onboard his gorgeous train...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.80,0:12:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,离他的办公室\Nand far away from him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,远远的\Nat the home office...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.40,0:12:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,置身于觥筹交错\Nconsigned to wine and dine
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.92,0:12:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,美人权贵之中\Nhandsome officials for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.36,0:12:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,裙带关系也是门艺术\NThere is an art to nepotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.76,0:12:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你在这方面可是大师\NAnd you are its Michelangelo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛先生\NMr. Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.88,0:12:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你也是妓女吗\NAre you a prostitute as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.08,0:12:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,当然不是\NCertainly not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.56,0:12:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这家伙打扰到你了吗\NIs this man bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,快了\NHe is about to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.16,0:12:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你是英国领事馆的人\NYou are from the British consulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.68,0:12:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 先生 是关于卡斯纳的案子\NI am, sir. It is the Kassner case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.96,0:12:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,您怎么知道\NWhy, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.44,0:13:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我的猜测是对的吗\NI was correct in certain predictions?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.72,0:13:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,准确无误\NQuite.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.68,0:13:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我不需要读这份电报\NI do not need to read the telegram.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.08,0:13:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,真有趣\NOh, how fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,是有人出轨了还是死了\NDid someone cheat, or die?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,很不幸 两者都是\NUnfortunately, both.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.08,0:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,有人\NSomeone has...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.60,0:13:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,搅乱了我期待已久的假期\Ninterrupted my longing for rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.36,0:13:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,看来我今晚得和你一起走了 布克\NIt appears that I must travel with you tonight, Bouc.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,能给我在东方快车上找个包厢吗\NCan you find me a cabin on the Orient Express?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.92,0:13:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我的朋友\NMy friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.16,0:13:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,别的我不敢说 大冬天里\NI may not be good for much, but I sure as hell
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的列车上\Ncan get you a bed on my train...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.56,0:13:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,给你找个床铺绝不成问题 三天行程\Nin the dead of winter. Three days...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,让你无忧无虑 不用想着那些罪案了 你会喜欢的\Nfree of care, concern or crime. You will love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.24,0:13:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,女士 很高兴认识你\NMademoiselle, it has been a pleasure. Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.52,0:13:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,您的行李已经取走了\NYour luggage has been collected
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.40,0:13:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,路费也已经付了\Nand your expenses paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,您坐到加来下车\NYou will be met at Calais...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.04,0:13:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,有人会送您到多佛\Nand then escorted to Dover,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.52,0:13:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,然后再坐火车到伦敦维多利亚车站\Nand then by rail to London Victoria.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.88,0:13:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,请允许我郑重地向您表达\NI would like to formally
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.32,0:13:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,请别再说了\Nexpress gratitude. Please, don't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,越说越烦\NYou make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,这是给你的小费 伙计 - 谢谢 马奎兹先生\NHere's a tip for you, pal. Thank you, Mr. Marquez.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.76,0:13:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我都没帮你搬行李\NI didn't even carry your luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.00,0:14:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这一周我过得很愉快\NOh, I had a good week.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.36,0:14:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,走运的时候就得庆祝\NWe celebrate when fortune smiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.00,0:14:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,好运就得拿来分享\Nand we share the good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,记得多说说我们美国人的好话\NRemember to say nice things about us Americans, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.72,0:14:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.00,0:14:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 站住\NHey, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好 先生\NMonsieur, bonsoir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.36,0:14:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生\NFor you, Mr. Ratchett,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.64,0:14:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,为您准备了我们这儿最好的位置\Nthe best table in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.60,0:14:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就在这儿 先生 最好的座位\NJust here, sir. The very best table.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我要坐那边\NNo, I want that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 马斯特曼 都安排妥了\NHey, Masterman. You got everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.60,0:14:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那还用问吗 麦奎因先生\NKind of you to inquire, Mr. MacQueen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.76,0:14:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来不会出差错\NI do not make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天呐 是安德烈伯爵\NOh, my goodness! It's Count Andrenyi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,快来 快来\NCome, come, come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.08,0:14:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我在蒙特克里斯托看过您的舞蹈\NI saw you dance at the Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.92,0:14:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我能给您拍张照吗\NCould I take your photograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,别 别打脸\NPlease, my face, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.96,0:15:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.68,0:15:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,新普伦东方快车\NThe Simplon Orient Express...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,经停索非亚 尼什 贝尔格莱德 温科夫齐 布罗德\Nwith stops in Sofia, Niš, Belgrade, Vinkovci, Brod...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.24,0:15:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,可中转至布加勒斯特 萨格勒布\Nwith transfers to Bucharest, Zagreb,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.52,0:15:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,的里雅斯特 威尼斯 米兰 洛桑\NTrieste, Venezia, Milan, Lausanne...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.36,0:15:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,第戎 巴黎 布伦 加来\NDijon, Paris, Boulogne, Calais...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.72,0:15:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,可接驳前往多佛及伦敦\Nwith connection to Dover and London,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.20,0:15:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,列车十五分钟后发车\Nleaves in fifteen minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:15:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 米歇尔 有贵客来了\NThis way, Michel! Precious cargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.72,0:16:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我要一间头等包厢\NI need a first-class compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.56,0:16:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,好好照顾我的朋友\NGive special care to my friend, Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,要像熊猫一样的国宝级待遇\NI want him pampered like a zoo panda.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.20,0:16:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,可是布克先生 席位已经满了\NBut Monsieur Bouc, we are fully booked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.28,0:16:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,没位置了\NThere's no space left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.40,0:16:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,想办法腾出来 可以安排11号包厢\NThen we make space. He can have the number eleven.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那里一般都安排给政府人员\NThe eleven is always kept open for official use.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,非常舒适\NIt's very comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,11号有人了\NEleven is taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.92,0:16:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,两天前一名奥地利教授定的\NThe Austrian professor booked it two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,整趟列车就找不到\NThere is not one first-class
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,一个头等包厢吗\Nsleeper car on the whole train?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.80,0:16:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 先生\NNegative, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.96,0:16:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 二等舱呢 - 一个空位都没有\NSecond-class? There's no space left at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.24,0:16:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,德贝汉小姐\NMademoiselle Debenham.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛先生 您也坐这趟列车吗\NMr. Poirot, are you joining us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.12,0:16:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,那得看他们俩谁说得赢谁\NIt depends who wins this debate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.28,0:16:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的乘客都到了吗\NHave all the passengers arrived?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,还差一位 哈里斯先生\NAll but one. Mr. Harris.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.48,0:16:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所有乘客\N"All passengers must check in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.92,0:16:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,至少提前半小时检票\N"at least one half hour prior to time of departure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.12,0:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,否则座位可能被收回\N"or their seat may be forfeit."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.92,0:16:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,已经不到半小时了 收回座位\NThe half hour has passed. The seat is forfeit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.60,0:16:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,请把波洛先生的行李\NPlease take Monsieur Poirot's luggage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,送到3号包厢 和麦奎因先生一间\Nto number three with Mr. MacQueen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.84,0:16:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 布克 - 旅途愉快\NMerci, Bouc. Enjoy, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.08,0:16:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎您先生 谢谢\NWelcome, sir. Merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.32,0:16:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,数字3可不吉利\NNumber three is unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.48,0:16:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉女生 刚才无意冒犯\NApologies, madame. I meant no disrespect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,偶尔冒犯一下也没关系\NWell, you could try to mean a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.68,0:17:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,坐火车出行\NOne thing about train travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.80,0:17:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,难免会碰到一些人\Nyou're always knocking into somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.96,0:17:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,那样才有趣\NIt's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.24,0:17:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我还是想回去\NThough, I am looking forward to getting back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.80,0:17:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱旅行 辛辣的美食 异域风情 浪漫的邂逅是不错\NTravel is fine for spicy food, mosques, meeting men.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但到头来还是自己的床最舒服\NBut eventually, you just miss your own bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.12,0:17:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定有人会说我总是满世界地找老公\NI've been accused of husband hunting abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我还真不否认这点\NWell, I can't, in all honesty, deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.20,0:17:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然我喜欢独处 我是说真的\NI like my time alone, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.56,0:17:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不过 一个女人如果有点钱的话\NBut a lady has certain needs
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.72,0:17:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,她的需求就该被满足\Nthat deserve to be met if she has any money...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.60,0:17:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,最好还是定期满足\Nand preferably, on a regular basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.60,0:17:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,天呐 厨房着火了\NOh, my! Fire in the kitchen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.60,0:17:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,再会了 女士\NFarewell, madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.36,0:17:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好\NGood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.44,0:17:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好\NBonsoir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.40,0:17:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,9号包厢\NNumber nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好\NGood evening. Bonsoir, bonsoir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.76,0:17:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你好吗 晚上好\NHow you doing? Bonsoir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.56,0:17:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思\NOh. Excusez-moi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.16,0:17:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,没事 你先请\NNo, after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.96,0:18:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NMerci, merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.28,0:18:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,三号到了\NAh number three.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.72,0:18:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你是麦奎因先生吗\NYou are Mr MacQueen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.76,0:18:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我想你走错包厢了\NYeah. I think you might have the wrong berth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.32,0:18:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 你有什么事吗 先生\NSorry, is there a problem sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.84,0:18:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不 没事\NNo, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.52,0:18:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,列车满了\NThe train is full.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.68,0:18:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我们得当一回 怎么说来着 室友\NI think that we are, how do you say... "bunkies."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.40,0:18:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我也感到很失望 这儿还不错\NI am equally disappointed in you. This is nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.08,0:18:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,快来 小宝贝们\NCome along, darlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.52,0:19:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不行\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.52,0:19:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不行\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.28,0:19:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这间呢\NThis?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么行李还没送来\NWhy am I not yet unpacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.28,0:19:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,五分钟后发车\NFive minutes to departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.96,0:19:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,最后一次通知乘客\NFinal call for passengers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.96,0:19:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要不要给你梳毛啊\NShall we brush you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.92,0:19:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他们动作怎么这么慢\NWhat the hell is taking them so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.84,0:19:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,发车后让他们赶紧铺床\NSoon as we get out of here, have them make up the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.68,0:19:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,都安排好了 雷切特先生\NIt's already arranged, Mr. Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.00,0:19:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不 先把床铺好 把我的录音机拿来\NNo, I want the bed made. And bring my Dictaphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.92,0:19:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,连狗都上桌了\NDogs on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.28,0:19:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,真是我见过最恶心的事\NMost disgusting thing I've ever seen in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.64,0:19:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 先生 你去找麦奎因\NYes, sir. I want you to get MacQueen...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.40,0:19:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,让他把米兰那笔买卖的单据全都拿来\Nand have him bring every receipt from the Milan sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.12,0:19:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,现在就去 好的先生\NI want you to get it done. Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.56,0:19:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 马上就去\NI want you to get it done now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.00,0:20:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不是让你马上就去吗 - 马上 先生\NDid I say get it done now? Right away, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.64,0:21:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你最好小心点\N"Better watch yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,您的咖啡 雷切特先生\NYour coffee, Mr. Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,是谁干的\NWho did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.76,0:21:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\NI can't say, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.52,0:21:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好 哈伯德夫人\NGood evening, Mrs. Hubbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.12,0:21:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你好 马斯特曼\NHello there, Mr. Masterman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.76,0:21:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你好 女士\NWell, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.12,0:21:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你再这么看下去 我就要收费了\NEyes linger any longer, I'll have to charge rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.48,0:21:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我很乐意付钱\NI'll pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.44,0:22:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,继续喝吧\NMmm. Have another drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,让您不高兴了吗\NAre you insulted?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,失望罢了\NHmm. Disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.40,0:22:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有些人是长得不错\NSome men have a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.32,0:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他们只要能够做到\NAll they have to do is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,闭上嘴\Nkeep their mouth shut,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.72,0:22:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,就能得到他们想要的\Nand they can take home any prize they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.84,0:22:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜他们偏偏做不到这点\NStill, the mouth opens.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,没事吧 哈伯德夫人\NIs everything all right, Mrs. Hubbard?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.72,0:22:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得您的直觉非常敏锐\NYou have a strong intuition, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.92,0:22:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我第二任丈夫也这么说过\NMy second husband used to say just so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.00,0:22:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 应该是第一任\NHold that, it was my first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.16,0:22:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.24,0:22:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他是我见过最聪明的男人\NBrightest man I ever met.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.20,0:22:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,长得像萝卜 不过我也爱过那颗萝卜\NFace like a turnip, but I loved that turnip.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.84,0:22:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,和您聊天很愉快\NIt was nice to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.36,0:23:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,晚安\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.68,0:23:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛先生\NMonsieur Poirot?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.40,0:23:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,请进 米歇尔\NEntrez, Pierre Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.60,0:23:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,您醒了\NVoilà.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.72,0:23:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,晚餐时\NWhen you take supper...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.80,0:23:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我会把麦奎因先生的东西\NI will move Monsieur MacQueen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.96,0:23:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,搬到布克先生的包厢\Ninto Monsieur Bouc's compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.16,0:23:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,您享受头等舱待遇\NYou travel first class, monsieur.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.24,0:23:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,太棒了 谢谢\NAh, impeccable. Merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.68,0:23:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,用餐愉快\NBon appétit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.56,0:24:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,下午好\NGood afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.04,0:24:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,哈伯德夫人\NAh, Mrs. Hubbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.48,0:24:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,下午好\NGood afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.40,0:24:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,请慢用\NThere we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.84,0:24:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,敬我们乘坐的东方快车\NCompliments of the Orient Express.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.76,0:24:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 布克先生\NThank you, Mr. Bouc.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.44,0:24:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么需要 随时告诉我\NI am here for all of your needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.76,0:24:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不 谢谢 我不喝酒\NNo, thank you. I do not drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.28,0:24:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,您不能喝酒吗\NIt does not agree with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.76,0:24:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想远离罪孽\NSin does not agree with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.72,0:24:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,恶习永远都是魔鬼的温床\NVice is where the devil finds his darlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.12,0:24:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,那我就不打扰您了\NWe should no longer speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.88,0:24:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,下午好\NGood afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.80,0:24:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,先生 要不要来杯开胃酒\NMonsieur. How about a apéritif?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.52,0:24:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜我已经和火车上的负责人\NI regret I have an appointment
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.36,0:24:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,约好了见面\Nwith the director of the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.52,0:24:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他很快就要走了\NHe was gonna leave anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.08,0:24:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,没事 先生\NPlease, sir. Madame, madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.24,0:24:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,女士 女士\NMadame, madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:24:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,都安顿好了吗\NAll settled in?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.16,0:24:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,一切如广告所说\NAh, merci! As advertised.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.04,0:25:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不过 车上最好的可不是食物\NAnd yet, the best things on the train are not food.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.24,0:25:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这实际上 就是\NYou know there's something about...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.56,0:25:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一群陌生人机缘巧合地坐上了同一趟列车\Na tangle of strangers pressed together
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.36,0:25:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一待就是几天\Nfor days on end, with nothing in common...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.88,0:25:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,除了这点之外 他们毫无关联\Nbut the need to go from one place to another...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.04,0:25:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,下车后就再也不见\Nthen never to see each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.28,0:25:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,闲来无聊加上萍水相逢\NBoredom plus anonymity plus a...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.60,0:25:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,再配上不间断的晃动\Nconstant, gentle rocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.60,0:25:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就你这样很难成大事\NWith your hobbies, you will never amount to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.44,0:25:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我倒希望是这样\NGod, I hope so. Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.08,0:25:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,给我点一道鱼\NOrder me the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.08,0:25:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,把石斑鱼换成比目鱼\NUm, exchange grouper for sole,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.56,0:25:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,再把莴苣换成土豆\Nescarole for the potato, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.08,0:25:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,还有 牛肉汁换成白汁\Nthe beef sauce for the velouté.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.64,0:25:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,服务员 这听上去很棒 给我也来一份\NGarçon, that sounds superb. The same for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.80,0:25:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,德拉戈米罗夫公主\NThe Princess Dragomiroff.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.20,0:25:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我为了钱和人结婚\NYou know, if I ever were to marry for money,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.04,0:25:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,就找她这么有钱的\NI'd marry for that much money.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.72,0:25:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,早上我给达莉娅梳了毛\NI brushed Dalia this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.12,0:25:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我让你给我的小狗梳毛\NNo, you tortured my darling doggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.92,0:25:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你却在折磨她\NI asked you to brush her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.32,0:26:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你还是爱看狄更斯的书吗\NAre you still enjoying your Dickens?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.64,0:26:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,当然了 我的朋友\NVery much, mon ami.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.64,0:26:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你这样光顾着看书和破案\NYou know, with your books and your capers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.64,0:26:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,很容易就错过艳遇\Nyou are missing out on romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.48,0:26:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,艳遇永远都要付出代价\NRomance never goes unpunished.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.56,0:26:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前\NThere was, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.08,0:26:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,也爱过一个人\NThere was someone once.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.32,0:26:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望之后别再让我坐在那个人旁边了\NI would prefer, in the future, to be sat not with that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.36,0:26:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,物以类聚 人以群分\NLike should be seated with like.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.84,0:26:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我们并不是一类人\NWe are not alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.92,0:26:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不是所有人都会\NNot all of us are so concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.36,0:26:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,那么在意种族隔离 教授\Nwith the separateness of races, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.96,0:26:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我的坚持完全是\NIt is out of respect for all kinds
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.32,0:26:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,出于对所有种族的尊重\Nthat I prefer to keep them separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.00,0:26:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,如果把红酒和白酒混在一起\NTo mix your red wine and the white
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.04,0:26:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,两者就都毁了\Nwould be to ruin them both.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.20,0:27:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢桃红酒\NI like a good rosé.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.76,0:27:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你好吗 不介意\NHey, how you doing? Would you mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.92,0:27:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我坐下吧\Nif I joined you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.60,0:27:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,要知道 甜品是一种享受\NDessert is an indulgence...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.96,0:27:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,一个人独享的话就实在太蠢了\Nand I feel kinda silly and stupid indulging alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.08,0:27:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我一个人待着挺好的\NI am at my happiest alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.28,0:28:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,不过\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.64,0:28:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,看在你这份丹麦卷的份上\Nfor a small piece of your fragelité,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.52,0:28:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,一起吧\Nplease join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.76,0:28:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 不好意思 再拿把叉子\NOh, with pleasure. Excuse me, another fork?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.88,0:28:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直想找机会认识你 波洛先生\NI've been trying to make your acquaintance, Mr. Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.96,0:28:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NMerci.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.60,0:28:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来没有这么近距离的接触过名人\NI never ever sat so close to fame before.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.56,0:28:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,不对\NNo, I tell a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.80,0:28:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾和泰·柯布坐过一辆车\NOnce, I was on a bus with Ty Cobb.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.12,0:28:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,底特律的球员\NBall player, Detroit. Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.96,0:28:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你不介意我把顶上这些吃掉吧\NWould you mind if I have the little curly bit at the top?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.12,0:28:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你还挺奇葩的\NYou're an odd bird there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.44,0:28:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,真是一个怪人\NYou're a strange, peculiar man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.80,0:28:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,到了这把年纪\NI am of an age
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.96,0:28:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我很清楚自己想要什么 不要什么\Nwhere I know what I like and what I do not like.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.08,0:28:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,喜欢的东西尽情享受\NWhat I like, I enjoy enormously.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.12,0:28:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,不喜欢的绝不容忍\NWhat I dislike, I cannot abide.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.64,0:28:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,比如 谈生意前 人们都爱说的\NFor instance, the temporary pleasantries
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.28,0:28:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那些客套话 我就很讨厌\Nbefore what is determined to be a business discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.64,0:28:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你很有趣\NYou're fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:28:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.60,0:29:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我想雇你做一件事\NI would like to offer you a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.64,0:29:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,报纸上说\N"The avenger of the innocent."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.76,0:29:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你是 还人清白的复仇者\NIt's what they call you in the papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.16,0:29:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你是清白的吗\NAnd you are an innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.68,0:29:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个商人\NI'm a businessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.44,0:29:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,买卖艺术品 虽然我入行不久\NI'm an art dealer. I mean, I'm new to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.48,0:29:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不过新手总是运气不错\NBut my beginner's luck has panned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.16,0:29:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,文物 古董\NRelics, antiquities.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.92,0:29:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,地毯 稀奇古怪的玩意儿 东方的一些东西\NRugs, weird. Orientals.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.08,0:29:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我还是个新手 所以眼光难免比较业余\NI'm new to the game, so I got the amateur eyeball.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.68,0:29:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不过说实话 我有点看不惯那些\NBut I got a little problem with these, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.68,0:29:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,所谓的鉴定师\Nso-called appraisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.96,0:29:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,全都不可靠\NYou can't trust a one of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.16,0:29:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我的一些客户\NSome of my customers...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.04,0:29:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他们从我这买了东西\Nthey buy a piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.36,0:29:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但后来发现 那些东西可能不是真品\Nthey find out that they're not exactly original...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.68,0:29:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,其实也不能怪我\Nwhich is hardly my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.20,0:29:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不知道碦山丝巾会是假的\Nif a Kashan silk scarf is a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.04,0:29:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,对吧\NRight? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.28,0:29:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\NC'est bon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.88,0:30:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,但总之我有不少仇家\NBut I've managed to make a few enemies, is the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.56,0:30:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我收到几封信 有人在威胁我\NI got a few letters, people making threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.72,0:30:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得最有嫌疑的是那帮意大利人\NI think, most likely, it's the Italians.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.96,0:30:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我在米兰的时候 卖给他们一套东方地毯\NI sold them a set of Oriental carpets in Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.24,0:30:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 买家对货的来源不太满意\NAnd the buyers weren't so happy with the provenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.32,0:30:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,于是他们想把钱连本带利地要回去\NAnd they want their money back with interest, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.32,0:30:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,意大利人\NItalians.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.04,0:30:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这幅德行\NA guinea's a guinea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.40,0:30:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我眼前就出现了一位神探\NAnd then comes along the genius detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.16,0:30:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说我吧\NMe?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.60,0:30:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,对 你 赫拉克勒斯·波洛\NYes, you. Hercules Poirot. Hercule.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.52,0:30:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 我就直说吧\NHere's what I'd like to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.00,0:30:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我想雇你保护我的安全\NI would like to hire you to watch my back...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.20,0:30:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,直到我去了安全的地方\Nuntil I get someplace safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.52,0:30:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这钱挺容易赚的\NIt's easy money for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.92,0:30:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我也能安心度过旅途\NAnd it's peace of mind for me, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.92,0:30:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 明白了 - 那么?\NI understand. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.76,0:30:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我拒绝\NI refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.84,0:30:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,什么? 这可不好\NI'm sorry? That's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.12,0:31:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,可能我话没太说清楚\NMaybe I didn't make myself clear enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.52,0:31:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 有人想要我的命\NYou see, someone's out to get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.68,0:31:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我不是什么好人 甚至还差远了\NAnd I know I'm not the best guy born, not by a long shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.76,0:31:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,如果人死后真的有地狱\NAnd if there's a world after this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.44,0:31:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,到时候我会和你一样面对上帝的审判\NI will face judgment just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.80,0:31:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不过\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.40,0:31:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我可不想提前到那报道\NI ain't in no goddamn rush to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.20,0:31:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你是在拿枪指着我么 - 不\NYou're holding a gun on me? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.28,0:31:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,不是对着你 是对着全世界\NNot you. On the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.08,0:31:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我存在于这个世界 别对着我\NI exist in the world. Do not point a gun at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.64,0:31:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,一周给你10000块怎么样?\NHow's ten thousand sound for a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.48,0:31:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 您很慷慨 雷切特先生 我拒绝\NIt's a generous offer, Mr. Ratchett. I must decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.64,0:31:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,15000呢?\NFifteen thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.72,0:31:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 再说一遍 我拒绝\NYou didn't hear me. I decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.04,0:31:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,明白了\NOh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.40,0:31:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,大侦探嫌这点钱不够\NIt's not flashy enough for the great Hercules Poirot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.32,0:31:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不光彩\NNo flashbulbs...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.56,0:31:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你把假冒文物卖给不法之徒\NYou sell fakes to gangsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.64,0:31:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你要自己承担后果\NYou're suffering the consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.44,0:31:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我揪出恶人 不会保护他们\NI detect criminals. I do not protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.12,0:31:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你是觉得我的钱是脏钱咯\NSo you say "no" to my dirty money.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.40,0:31:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是拒绝你而已 雷切特先生\NI say "no" to you, Mr. Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.32,0:31:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这把枪的事吧 就因为这个?\NBusiness with the gun, right? Is that what it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.76,0:31:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,更多的是个人原因\NIt is far more personal than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.68,0:32:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢你这张脸\NI do not like your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.16,0:32:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,请原谅 我要走了\NIf you will excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.16,0:32:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢我的蛋糕么\NYou liked my cake, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.36,0:32:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,挺不错的\NThe cake was excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.84,0:32:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生 祝您下午愉快\NHave a pleasant afternoon, Mr. Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.84,0:32:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.88,0:32:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,真冷啊\NOoh! Cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.08,0:33:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我亲爱的凯瑟琳\NMy sweet Katherine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.52,0:33:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我的挚爱\NMy love.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.40,0:33:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,狄更斯先生\NMr. Dickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.76,0:33:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生\NMr. Ratchett?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.28,0:33:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生\NMr. Ratchett?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.28,0:33:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么事\NIt's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.40,0:33:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 先生\NVery good sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.12,0:33:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,晚安\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.28,0:34:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,又怎么了\NMrs. Hubbard?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.32,0:34:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,哈伯德夫人 还会有谁呢\NIt's always Mrs. Hubbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.40,0:34:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,哈伯德夫人\NMrs. Hubbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.52,0:35:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我们死了吗\NDid we die?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.52,0:35:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 我们的列车脱轨了\NLadies and gentlemen, the train has been derailed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.88,0:35:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吧 马奎兹先生\NAre you all right, Mr. Marquez?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.52,0:35:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我没事 我没事 谢谢\NI'm fine. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.52,0:35:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,请留在车厢里\NYou'll be safest in your cabins.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.68,0:35:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,明天一早布克先生会和\NMr. Bouc will speak to you all...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.16,0:35:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,大家说明情况\Nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.32,0:35:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,安全起见请留在包厢里\NPlease, you will be safest in your cabins.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.68,0:35:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.04,0:35:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会死么\NAre we gonna die?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.56,0:35:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我的凯瑟琳\NMy Katherine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.56,0:35:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我美丽的\NMy beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.64,0:36:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们 先生们 恐怕\NLadies and gentlemen, I am afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.80,0:36:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的列车暂时还不能重新启程\Nthat our train is still unable to go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.48,0:36:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,一动就掉下去了\NYeah, except down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.72,0:36:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还要在这儿等多久\NHow long are we supposed to just sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.48,0:36:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 总得有人做些什么吧\NYes, someone must be doing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.04,0:36:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我确实该做些什么 可我本人什么都不用做\NOf course I am doing something. I am doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.08,0:36:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,准确来说两小时十分钟之前\NPrecisely two hours and ten minutes ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.60,0:36:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,布罗德的站长见我们没能准时抵达\Nwhen we did not arrive in Brod as scheduled...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.80,0:36:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他一定已经猜到了我们的处境\Nthe station master will have surmised our situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.04,0:36:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他会派人来扶正列车\Nand already dispatched a team to excavate the engine...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.88,0:36:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,清理道路 好让我们继续前行\Nclear our path, and send us on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.28,0:36:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在那之前 我保证\NUntil then, I assure you...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.64,0:36:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,大家一定会享受到温暖而又舒适的列车服务\Nwe will all be made warm and fed and comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.72,0:37:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以走过去\NWe could walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.00,0:37:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,走不了几步我们就会被冻死\NWe could die of exposure trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.84,0:37:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我之后还要赶去别的地方\NI have a connection to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.92,0:37:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我的船后天从法国出发\NMy boat sails day after tomorrow from France.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.28,0:37:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我赌你赶不上了 我也到不了伦敦\NWithout you, I'd wager. Or me in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.72,0:37:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你得对我损失的时间负责 布克先生\NI hold you accountable for my loss of time, Mr. Bouc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.40,0:37:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,女士 您不能把天气因素怪到我头上\NMadam, you cannot hold me accountable for the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.20,0:37:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,谁让你是这儿管事的呢\NOf course I can. You're the one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.44,0:37:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我在都灵的会议怎么办\NAnd my conference in Turin?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.76,0:37:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我还得赶去索肖的汽车工厂呢\NAnd I was to meet at the auto factory in Sochaux.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.48,0:37:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,有些事冥冥中自有定数\NYes, some things, they are in God's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.44,0:37:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能不能安全抵达目的地\NIt is not for us to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.64,0:37:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,不由我们说了算\Nif we deserve to arrive safely at our destination...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.20,0:37:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,又或者像邪恶天使路西法那样 我们注定坠落\Nor if, like Lucifer, we must fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.08,0:37:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,您的早餐 雷切特先生\NBreakfast for you, Mr. Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.92,0:37:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,早 马斯特曼先生\NAh, Bonjour, Mr. Masterman.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.48,0:37:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,出什么事了吗\NThere is a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.04,0:38:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道 先生\NI can't say, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.64,0:38:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生\NMr. Ratchett?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.12,0:38:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.28,0:38:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,里面有冷风\NThat is cold air.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.96,0:38:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,请让布克先生赶紧过来\NPlease bring Monsieur Bouc immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.00,0:38:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,还有阿巴斯诺特医生\Nand also Dr. Arbuthnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.60,0:38:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天呐\NGood God!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.48,0:38:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,除了尸体 什么都别碰\NTouch nothing else, only the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.32,0:38:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这太可怕了\NMy God, this is horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.60,0:38:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,先是大雪 现在又...\NFirst the snow, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.24,0:38:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这下我必须得到\NI'll have to meet with the police
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.44,0:38:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,站台和警察说明一下情况\Nand make some statement in some grimy station.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.32,0:39:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,现在有人死在了这儿\NAnd a man has died.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.32,0:39:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,有人死在了这儿\NAnd a man has died.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.92,0:39:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是被捅死的\NHe was stabbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.20,0:39:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,被一把长刀\NLong, straight-edged knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.52,0:39:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有多处伤口 有的很浅\NMultiple stab wounds, some shallow,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.24,0:39:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,有的径直刺穿了肌肉\Nsome cut clean through muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.88,0:39:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,左撇子还是右撇子\NLeft-hand side or right-hand side?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.48,0:39:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,问题就在这儿\NThat's the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.36,0:39:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手似乎是\NIt appears the killer
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.20,0:39:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,闭着眼睛在乱捅一气\Nmaybe closed his eyes and struck blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.72,0:39:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你能不能推算一下死亡时间\NCan you estimate the time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.32,0:39:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,说不准 里面窗户又开着\NIt's hard to say with the window open...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.88,0:39:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不过 我觉得应该是午夜到两点之间\Nbut my best guess is between midnight and 2:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.88,0:39:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,可没人进出过他的包厢\NBut no one went in his compartment then.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.28,0:39:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我整晚坐在外面\NI sat in my seat all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.48,0:39:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,有人进出我一定会看到 这不可能\NI would have seen if someone went in. It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.20,0:39:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 医生 请回餐车去吧\NThank you, Doctor. Please, return to the dining car.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.20,0:39:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,米歇尔 封锁他的包厢\NMichel, secure this carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.44,0:39:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛\NPoirot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.12,0:39:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你得帮我 朋友\NI need your help, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.48,0:39:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你得找出凶手\NYou have to find who did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.08,0:39:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,求你了 我代表东方快车公司\NPlease, I implore you,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.28,0:39:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,恳求你\Non behalf of the Orient Express.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.00,0:39:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,等警察到了\NWhen the police arrive,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.12,0:39:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以直接告诉他们真相\Nwe can present them with the case closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.28,0:39:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,现在只有你才能救我\NYou are the only one who can save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.48,0:40:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你的信任让我非常感动\NYour faith touches me, mon cher.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.72,0:40:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但我这次是来休假的\NBut I must have this rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.64,0:40:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以把它看作是海边的猜谜游戏\NWell, think of it as a little beachside puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.88,0:40:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你根本就不用太费力气\NThat's nothing to your mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.92,0:40:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你只要看一眼乘客的出身背景\NYou look up the antecedents of the passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.16,0:40:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,看看他们有没有说谎\NYou establish their bona fides.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.40,0:40:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,然后该干吗就干吗\NThen you do what you do. You... You... You...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.76,0:40:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以坐在椅子里 然后 你边吃蛋糕边思考\NYou sit in a chair and you eat your cake...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.24,0:40:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,直到真相浮出水面了\Nand you think until the solution presents itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.60,0:40:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不然在这冰天雪地里你还能干吗\NWhat else are you going to do while we sit here in the snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.56,0:40:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,没有东西刺激你的大脑\NWithout constant stimulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.72,0:40:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你的脑细胞会饿死的\Nyour little gray cells will starve and die.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.28,0:40:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为就这么简单 坐在椅子里\NYou think that is what I do? I sit in a chair...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.72,0:40:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,吃着小蛋糕\Nand I have a little piece of cake,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.80,0:40:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,然后就破案了\Nand then I come up with a great idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.12,0:40:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道你是怎么破案的 - 我还要读狄更斯\NI don't know what you do. I have my Dickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.64,0:40:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,去你的狄更斯\NDamn your Dickens!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.08,0:40:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,如果把案子交给警察\NIf we leave this to the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.32,0:40:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会随便找个替罪羊\Nthey will choose a culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.64,0:40:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,无论他是不是真凶 那人都得死\Nright or wrong, and they will hang him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.88,0:40:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,很可能是马奎兹\NMost probably Mr. Marquez...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.24,0:40:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不为什么 就因为他有个拉丁裔的名字\Nfor no other reason than his name is Marquez.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.56,0:40:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,或者那位医生 就因为他的肤色\NOr Dr. Arbuthnot for the color of his skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.68,0:40:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,现在只有你能主持公道\NYou are the only one who can bring justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.96,0:40:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,给我一张车厢的图纸\NLet me have a map of this coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.04,0:40:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.12,0:41:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人的护照 没问题\NEvery passport. Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.20,0:41:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,安排一下 我要询问每一名乘客\NInterviews arranged with all of our passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.24,0:41:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,找出证据 记录下时间和顺序 揪出真凶\NEvidence, order and method, until one culprit emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.48,0:41:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能容忍谋杀行为 我的朋友\NI do not approve of murder, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.48,0:41:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,每天我们\NEvery day, we meet people
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.56,0:41:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,都会遇到一些败类\Nthe world could do better without...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.68,0:41:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,可我们不能杀死他们\Nyet we do not kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.08,0:41:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们应该有别于野兽\NWe must be better than the beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.52,0:41:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就让我们找出这个凶手吧\NSo let us find this killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.12,0:41:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,发生什么了\NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.20,0:41:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 有件事想告知大家\NLadies and gentlemen, allow me to, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.16,0:41:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎我们的厄运不仅仅只是这场大雪\NIt appears that our bad luck has worsened.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.00,0:41:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,很不幸\NThat is...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.16,0:41:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有一名乘客死在了车上\NA passenger has died on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.32,0:41:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生\NMonsieur Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.20,0:41:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,看来他们还是得逞了\NLooks like they got him after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.00,0:41:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得他是被谋杀的\NYou assume he was killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.12,0:41:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.84,0:41:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 他身体很健康\NI just mean he was in perfectly good health.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.68,0:41:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不过却得罪了不少人\NHe had his enemies, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.36,0:41:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 他是被谋杀的\NIndeed, he did. He was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.96,0:41:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,天呐 谋杀 在这儿\NGood God. Murder, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.96,0:42:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 女士\NAlas, madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.36,0:42:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,愿上帝保佑他安息\NGod rest his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.24,0:42:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,昨天半夜有人\NSomeone was rummaging around my cabin
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.12,0:42:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,闯进了我的包厢\Nin the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.56,0:42:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,可没人相信我\NNobody would believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.64,0:42:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,到底怎么回事\NWhat is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.88,0:42:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,既然我们哪儿都去不了\NAs we are snowbound,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.04,0:42:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,布克先生已经\NI have elected to take the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.44,0:42:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,委托我调查此案并找出真凶\Nand find for my friend, Monsieur Bouc, the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.12,0:42:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么是你\NAnd why you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.88,0:42:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,*我是赫尔克里·波洛\NMy name is Hercule Poirot...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.92,0:42:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是这个世上最伟大的侦探\Nand I am probably the greatest detective in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.08,0:42:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我会单独找你们谈话\NI will speak to all of you in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.44,0:42:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在\NFor the moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.92,0:42:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我建议你们\NI must recommend that you remain
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.16,0:42:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,回到包厢把门锁上\Nin your compartments with the doors locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.72,0:42:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,感觉像囚犯一样\NI feel like a prisoner here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.56,0:42:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这是为了你们自身的安全\NIt is for your own safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.12,0:42:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,如果这是一起谋杀案\NIf there was a murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.40,0:42:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就一定会有凶手\Nthen there was a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.40,0:42:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,而他就在我们身边\NThe murderer is with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.80,0:42:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他在列车上 就现在\Non the train, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.76,0:43:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,车厢与车厢之间的门晚上都会上锁对吧\NThe doors between coaches were locked at night, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.16,0:43:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 我亲自锁的\NAbsolutely. Done myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.16,0:43:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,已经搜过了\NThe train's been searched.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.32,0:43:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,没人躲在车顶或者车底\NThere's no one hiding on it or under it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.72,0:43:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我们就可以把范围\NWe can therefore limit our investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.12,0:43:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,缩小到加来车厢的那几位乘客了\Nto the occupants of the Calais coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.72,0:43:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,布克你来帮我\NBouc, you will assist me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.80,0:43:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,只有你睡在了别的车厢\NAs the only traveler who slept in another coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.60,0:43:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你是唯一没有嫌疑的人\Nyou are the only one who is not a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.20,0:43:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,麦奎因先生 您一定要现在喝酒吗\NMr. MacQueen, is this really the time for drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.84,0:43:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我的老板死了\NMy boss is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.76,0:43:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我丢了饭碗\NI'm out of a job,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.48,0:43:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,而你们像看犯人一样看着我\Nand you're looking at me like I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.28,0:43:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我们并没有提出指控\NWe make no accusations.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.68,0:43:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你了解他 所以从你这儿\NYou knew him, so from here
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.04,0:43:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能获得重要信息\Nwe must glean the essential facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.52,0:43:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你们是亲戚吗\NWere you his relative?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.16,0:43:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我是他秘书\NNo, his secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.48,0:43:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,帮他订票 替他点牛排\NBook his travel, order his steaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.00,0:43:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,他吃过的牛排\NThe man ate more steak
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.32,0:43:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,比我这辈子见过的还要多\Nthan I've ever seen in my entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.60,0:43:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他做古董生意\NHe was in antiques.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.92,0:43:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他没有文物方面的资历\NHe had no qualification for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.56,0:43:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,没有眼光 也不会外语\Nnot the eye or the languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.28,0:44:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不会记账\NTruth is, he had no head for business, accounting...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.84,0:44:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都不懂\Nnone of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.32,0:44:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,全都是我在打理\NI took care of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.68,0:44:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你在他这儿工作多久了\NHow long were you in his employ?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.32,0:44:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,差20天就满一年了\NTwenty days shy of a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.32,0:44:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我受不了美国的禁酒令\NProhibition wasn't to my taste...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.92,0:44:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我 选择了去国外 还负了债\Nso I found myself overseas, and in debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.20,0:44:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我是学法律出身的\NI'm a lawyer by education...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.96,0:44:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜我不是这块料\Nnot disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.96,0:44:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,还搞得一团糟\NI was downright awful at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.88,0:44:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢他的为人吗\NYou were fond of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.32,0:44:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢的是他的钱\NI was fond of his money.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.88,0:44:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他为人粗俗\NRatchett was crude...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.56,0:44:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,挑剔 爱骂人 很可能还犯过罪\Ndemanding, insulting, and most likely a felon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.44,0:44:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你最后见到他是什么时候\NWhen did you last see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.44,0:44:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,应该是刚过十点\NIt must have been just after 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.52,0:44:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他叫我过去核查一遍意大利的生意\NHe called me in to go over our sales in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.76,0:44:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,在米兰卖出的那些赝品\NMilan, the sale of forgeries?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.52,0:44:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,对 没错\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.52,0:44:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他想让我查看一下账目\NHe wanted to look over the accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.32,0:44:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我得给他做翻译\NI had to translate everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.24,0:44:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,合同是法文写的\Nas the contracts were in French
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.36,0:44:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他一个字都看不懂\Nand he didn't speak a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.68,0:45:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,列车停靠在温科夫齐时\NAnd when we stopped at Vinkovci...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.20,0:45:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我和黑人医生聊了会儿\NI struck up a chat with the colored doctor, Arbuthnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.96,0:45:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还喝了几杯 活动一下腿脚\NAnd we had a couple of drinks, stretched our legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.24,0:45:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我不太赞同\NHe had some...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.40,0:45:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他对斯大林的看法 所以想纠正他\Nodd opinions about Stalin I had to turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.28,0:45:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我对那位医生没有种族偏见\NI don't hold a man's race against him,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.88,0:45:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不怎么喜欢英国佬\Nbut I don't often take to Britishers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.84,0:45:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你们几点分开的\NWhen did your party end?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.56,0:45:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他是在两点后走的\NHe left just after 2:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.52,0:45:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道雷切特的仇家\NDid you know of any specific enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.04,0:45:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,具体有谁吗\NRatchett might have had?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.88,0:45:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,天呐\NGosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.40,0:45:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,多了去了\NPick a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.92,0:45:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,他说有人威胁他是吧\NHe confided he had been threatened?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.80,0:45:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他收到了几封恐吓信\NHe got a couple of nasty letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.68,0:45:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我这里正好有几封 要看吗\NI have them if you like. Some, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.16,0:45:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,其它的都被他撕了\NHe tore up the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.44,0:45:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一把火烧了\NThrew them into the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.76,0:45:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,就这些\NThat's them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.04,0:45:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 麦奎因先生\NMerci, Mr. MacQueen.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.16,0:45:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NUh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.32,0:45:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如果还有别的问题\NIf we have any further questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.52,0:45:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会再来找你的\Nwe will call for you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.00,0:46:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你们怀疑过那个拉丁人\NHave you considered the Latin man?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.44,0:46:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,马奎兹吗 那家伙挺可疑的\NMarquez. Hell of a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.16,0:46:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,而且你们也知道\NAnd, well, you know, his kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.84,0:46:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,拉丁人并不反感杀人\Nthey don't have the same distaste for murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.36,0:46:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,历史经验是这样的\Nhistorically speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.20,0:46:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你不是说你没有种族偏见吗\NYou said you don't hold a man's race against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.20,0:46:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,或许\NI suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.60,0:46:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,得看是哪个种族\Ndepends on the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.88,0:46:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他本来表现得还不错\NAnd he was doing so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.72,0:46:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得是他?  现在还太早\NYou think it's MacQueen? Too early to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.64,0:46:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,很难想象他会有底气\NI admit, I cannot see him
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.76,0:46:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,朝一个人连捅12刀\Nstabbing a man twelve times in a frenzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.20,0:46:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是酒精作祟  不然还会是谁\NNot sober, anyway. Who did it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.80,0:46:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我还不知道 得问一个人\NI do not know yet. It is time we ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.60,0:46:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,去问谁 - 受害者的尸体\NAsk who? The victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.12,0:47:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,受害者被捅了12刀\NHe has twelve stab wounds
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.00,0:47:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,正如医生所说伤口深浅不一\Nand, as Arbuthnot said, they are patternless.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.76,0:47:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是医生干的\NIf the doctor is guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.08,0:47:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,至少在这点上\Nhe certainly did not let it influence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.48,0:47:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,并没有说假话\Nhis responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.76,0:47:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,看这儿 停在了一点15\NHey, the watch. Stopped at 1:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.00,0:47:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,和死亡时间一致\NNow that agrees with the doctor on the time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.84,0:47:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能 确实有可能\NHmm. It is possible, yes. Certainly possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.96,0:47:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白\NI don't quite understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.12,0:47:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我自己也不明白\NI do not understand, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.44,0:47:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,至今毫无头绪\NI understand nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.76,0:47:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你看这两道伤口\NIf you look at these two wounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.80,0:47:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,看得出来力道很大 插得很深 但流血很少\Nthey are powerful and deep, and yet there is little blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.16,0:47:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,可这明明是一次疯狂的袭击\NBut this was a frenzied attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.96,0:47:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手连续捅了很多刀\NLashing here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.68,0:47:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,用力不均但却极端暴力\NNo pattern at all, just extreme violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.64,0:47:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,而我们的死者\NAnd during all this, our victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.44,0:47:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,为人暴躁又焦虑 还喝了那么多咖啡\Nvigorous and anxious and full of coffee...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.72,0:47:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,却在这一过程静静的躺在这儿 丝毫没有反抗\Nmerely lies still and accepts death without struggle...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.20,0:47:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,而与此同时\Nwhen he also has here...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.12,0:47:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他的枕头下面还准备了防身用的武器\Nthe means by which he might defend himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.12,0:48:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,给你拿着\NFor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.96,0:48:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,再来看看这个\NNow, let us see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.64,0:48:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,巴比妥 服用了会让人昏睡\NBarbital. The Mickey slipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.96,0:48:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,这样他就没法用手枪了\NDrugged him so he couldn't use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.68,0:48:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,同时这儿还有一条女士手帕\NAnd later around here, a lady's handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.16,0:48:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,十分贵重 手工制作\NAn objet de luxe, handmade.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.28,0:48:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在巴黎要卖200法郎\NBoom, two hundred francs in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.80,0:48:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,上面还绣了一个大写字母“H"\NAnd she even has an initial, "H."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.48,0:48:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,还有这玩意儿\NAnd our little friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.00,0:48:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,清烟斗的通条 又一个线索\Nthe pipe cleaner. Another clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.96,0:48:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,对 犯人留下了那么多显而易见的线索\NYes, a riot of clues dropped most conveniently.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.80,0:48:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但或许事实上只有一个才是真的\NYet only one appears, however, to be perhaps genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,烟灰缸里\NAnd maybe this ashtray provides
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.16,0:48:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,不经意地留下的蛛丝马迹\Nthe accidental breadcrumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.68,0:48:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一张烧焦的字条\NA charred fragment of a note.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.84,0:48:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,也可能是凶手试图毁灭的证据\NAn attempt, perhaps, to burn evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.68,0:48:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢先生\NMerci, monsieur.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.52,0:48:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以借用一下工具吧\NWe may borrow your equipment, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.16,0:48:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,谢了\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.00,0:48:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 谢谢\NMerci, merci.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.64,0:49:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,相比现场留下了什么证物\NNow, I prefer to understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.24,0:49:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我更好奇为什么会把它们留在案发现场\Nwhy a clue is left rather than what the object is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.16,0:49:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,要从事物发内部探寻真相 而不是看表象\NWe seek the truth from within, not without.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.40,0:49:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,所以现在\NIn this case, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.64,0:49:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可能需要借助一下科学的力量\NI may welcome a little scientific assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.00,0:49:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你来帮我控制火焰\NYou will adjust the flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.04,0:49:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,又是一封恐吓信\NIt's just another one of those nasty letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.56,0:49:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你错了 我的朋友\NYou are mistaken, mon ami.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.88,0:49:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这些文字另有玄机\NThis one has a secret to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.28,0:49:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,看\NLook.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.92,0:49:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你的手上沾着斯特朗的血 你会丧命\N"As a strong blood is on hand, you will die."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.40,0:49:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思\NWhat does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.60,0:49:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我来 布克\NCome with me, Bouc.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.88,0:49:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把缺失的部分补上\NLet us fill in the gaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.08,0:49:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这不再是海边的猜谜游戏了\NThis was never a beachside puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.72,0:49:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道死者的真正身份了\NI know the dead man's real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.44,0:50:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他不叫雷切特 而叫卡萨蒂\NIt is not Ratchett, but Cassetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.08,0:50:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我听过这名字\NI know that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.64,0:50:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,那你一定也听过阿姆斯特朗这名字\NThen you will also know the name Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.24,0:50:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说阿姆斯特朗惨案\NThe Armstrong case?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.44,0:50:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那起案子震惊了全世界\NThe story shocked the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.60,0:50:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,两年前\NTwo years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.76,0:50:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,著名飞行员 约翰·阿姆斯特朗上校\Nthe renowned pilot, Colonel John Armstrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.08,0:50:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,和妻子索尼娅\Nand his wife, Sonia,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.60,0:50:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,醒来后发现他们的独生女小黛西\Nwoke to find their only child, little Daisy...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.28,0:50:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,在睡梦中遭人绑架\Ntaken from her crib as she slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.56,0:50:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,走投无路的\NDesperate...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.80,0:50:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗夫妇支付了赎金\Nthe Armstrongs paid the ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.76,0:50:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但不久后 人们还是找到了黛西的尸体\NBut soon after, Daisy was found murdered by...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.96,0:50:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手就是雷切特 也就是卡萨蒂\NRatchett, who was Cassetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.92,0:50:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,得知这一噩耗时\NSonia Armstrong was with child
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.96,0:50:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,索尼娅已经怀有身孕\Nwhen she received the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.80,0:50:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这一刺激导致婴儿早产\NThe shock sent her into premature labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,母子二人都没能活下来\NNeither she nor her baby survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.88,0:50:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道的 波洛\NHow do you know this, Poirot?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.60,0:50:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,因为是约翰·阿姆斯特朗告诉我的\NBecause John Armstrong told me so himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.12,0:50:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他写信给我请求帮助\NHe wrote to me to ask me for my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.12,0:50:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,当我收到那封信时\NBy the time I received his letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.32,0:51:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,已经太迟了\Nit was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.92,0:51:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,人们发现他中枪而亡\NHe was found dead of a gunshot wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.80,0:51:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是自杀\NSelf-inflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.92,0:51:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你手上沾着黛西·阿姆斯特朗的血\N"Daisy Armstrong's blood is on your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.08,0:51:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你会为此丧命\N"You will die for it."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.32,0:51:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,到头来的确如此\NIndeed, you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.00,0:51:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛先生 怎么了 米歇尔\NMonsieur Poirot? Yes, Michel.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.00,0:51:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,哈伯德夫人有话和你说\NMrs. Hubbard wants to speak to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.76,0:51:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经尽量拖住她了\NI held her as best as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.48,0:51:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,哈伯德夫人 抱歉 久等了\NAh, Mrs. Hubbard, I'm sorry to have kept you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.28,0:51:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,听说你有一肚子的火和一肚子的话要说\NYou have a head full of steam and a mouth full of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.48,0:51:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 算你说对了 这些话我今天\NYou're goddamn right, I do. What I have been trying...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.88,0:51:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一早就想对你说了\Nto tell you all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.88,0:51:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你们要找的那名凶手 昨晚去过我的包厢\NThe murderer was in my compartment last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.00,0:51:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为他会杀了我 的确有人丧命\NI thought I'd be killed. Turns out I might have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.48,0:51:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,只不过死的却是雷切特\Nonly he got Ratchett instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.40,0:51:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我在黑暗中惊醒\NI woke up in the dark, and I knew
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.72,0:51:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,发现包厢里有个男人\Nthere was a man in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.48,0:51:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定那是一个男人\NYou are certain it was a man?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.08,0:51:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道有男人在我房间的感觉是什么样的\NI know what it feels like to have a man in my bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.48,0:51:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉了列车员 可他却不相信我\NI told your conductor, and he wouldn't believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.48,0:51:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我说检查下\NI said, "Check the communication door
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.08,0:51:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我和雷切特包厢之间的连接门\N"between my room and Ratchett's.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.40,0:52:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手肯定从那儿跑了\N"He must have left through there."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.52,0:52:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不出所料 门并没有上锁\NSure enough, it was unbolted.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.80,0:52:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我特意锁好的\NI know I locked it...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.08,0:52:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,因为雷切特说了那些话\Nafter what Ratchett said.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.20,0:52:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他提了一些颇为露骨的要求\NHe made a rather overt overture.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.44,0:52:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你之前有没有听说过\NHave you perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.92,0:52:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗绑架案\Nheard of the Armstrong kidnapping?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.80,0:52:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这么骇人听闻\NYou couldn't avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.52,0:52:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,想不知道都难\NMorbid stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.96,0:52:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,杀害那孩子的凶手 卡萨蒂\NThe child's murderer, Cassetti...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.84,0:52:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,昨晚死了\Ndied last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.84,0:52:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,就是雷切特\NRatchett was the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.16,0:52:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我早就说过 我一看就知道他有问题\NI told you, I knew he was a rotten one.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.36,0:52:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你相信我吗\NYou do believe me...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.52,0:52:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我房里确实有人\Nabout the man in my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.84,0:52:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你觉得我是个蠢女人\NI'm aware you think I'm a silly woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.04,0:52:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,可是我有证据 是真的\NBut I have proof it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.08,0:52:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,这是东方快车\NIt is from the uniform...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.28,0:52:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,列车员制服上的\Nof an Orient Express conductor...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.96,0:52:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是米歇尔\Nbut it might have fallen from Michel's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.12,0:52:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,在你房间时落下的\Nwhen he was in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.60,0:52:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我的扣子没掉\NI'm not missing any.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.80,0:52:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我是在\NI found it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.88,0:52:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,床尾的被子上找到的\Nat the foot of my bed, on the cover...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.12,0:52:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,就在我睡觉的地方\Nright where I slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.12,0:52:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么看\NWhat do you call that?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.32,0:53:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,的确是有力证据 非常感谢哈伯德夫人\NI call it evidence. Thank you so much, Mrs. Hubbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.36,0:53:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你去过美国吗\NHave you ever been to America?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.92,0:53:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,去过一次\NOnce.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.64,0:53:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,几年前 呆了没几天\NYears ago, briefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.56,0:53:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,去那儿干嘛\NFor what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.48,0:53:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,去验证一个猜想 什么猜想\NTo confirm a suspicion. Which was?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.76,0:53:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜我不喜欢美国\NThat I wouldn't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.32,0:53:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,波士顿那边有个工作机会\NI was offered a post in Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.16,0:53:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但一到那儿我就直接回伦敦了\NSaw Boston, went straight back to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.00,0:53:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特不就是那儿的人吗\NIs that where Ratchett was from?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.40,0:53:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,波士顿 我并不知道这些\NBoston? I can't says I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.04,0:53:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一般不太会问别人\NIt wouldn't be proper...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.72,0:53:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这种问题\Nto ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.96,0:53:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,请继续\NCarry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.12,0:53:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我最后见到\NI last saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.68,0:53:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生应该是九点\NMr. Ratchett at nine o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.08,0:53:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我去送咖啡  把他的衣服挂好了\NI brought his coffee and hung up his clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.68,0:53:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜你牙疼犯了吧\NYou have a toothache, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.00,0:53:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我预约了这周回伦敦拔牙\NI've got an extraction booked in London this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.24,0:53:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生叮嘱我说这事不能再拖了\NMr. Ratchett insisted on not putting it off any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.92,0:53:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他说他受不了\NHe said he was tired of hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.20,0:53:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我哼哼唧唧的声音\Nmy suppressed groans.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.44,0:53:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这么有同情心的雷切特先生\NThis sympathetic Ratchett...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.72,0:54:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,平时晚上都会喝咖啡吗\Nwas it his usual practice to drink coffee at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.44,0:54:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,以前不会 不过他最近有点焦虑\NNot at all. But he'd been very agitated lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.88,0:54:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,总说要让自己保持警惕\NSaid he wanted to stay alert, especially so last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.96,0:54:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,尤其是昨晚他在包厢里发现了一封信\NHe found a letter in his compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.56,0:54:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这应该不是你做的吧\NPlease tell me you didn't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.72,0:54:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是我做的话\NIf I were to leave something unpleasant
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.24,0:54:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,恐怕就不只是\Non your pillow, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.56,0:54:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,留张纸条那么简单了\Nit would not be a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.16,0:54:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,咖啡\NCoffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.28,0:54:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,一名\NSurely, such a...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.88,0:54:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,称职 细心的男仆\Nproper and precise valet...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.84,0:54:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是绝不会那样和主人说话的\Nwould never speak to his master as you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.76,0:54:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,除非他知道 自己这份工作\NUnless he knew his career was coming to a sudden...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.36,0:54:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,很快就会结束\Nend.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.36,0:54:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜你不仅仅是牙疼吧\NNo mere toothache, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.24,0:54:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,肺癌\NThe lungs?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.16,0:54:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,是甲状腺\NThe thyroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.44,0:54:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,已经转移到了胃\NSpread now to stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.64,0:54:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,和我父亲一样 他死时比我还年轻五岁\NSame as got my father, five years younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.04,0:54:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,最多再活几个月\NMonths at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.40,0:55:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,医生说恐怕手术无法治愈\N"Inoperable, I'm afraid," said the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.56,0:55:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,突然间我再也不怕了\NAnd suddenly, I wasn't... afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.40,0:55:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我只想做一些想做的事\NI would only do what I wanted from here on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.60,0:55:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,说自己想说的话\NI speak my mind now.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.20,0:55:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,那杯咖啡\NThe coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.08,0:55:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,有人肯定朝里面下了镇定剂\NIt appears that his cup was laced with barbital.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.12,0:55:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你肯定会说\NYou, of course, will tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.24,0:55:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那不是你干的\Nthat you did not put it in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.36,0:55:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,当然不是我\NOf course I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.80,0:55:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么时候\NWhen and from where
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.08,0:55:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,从哪里拿的杯子和咖啡\Ndid you procure the coffee and the cups?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.44,0:55:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,就在厨房拿的\NIn the kitchen, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.96,0:55:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我晚餐时点的 说好九点去拿 就是那样\NI ordered it at dinner to be ready at 9:00, and so it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.32,0:55:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,在我之前谁都可能接触到那杯咖啡\NAnybody could have got a hold of it before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.00,0:55:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NMerci.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.20,0:55:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,马斯特曼先生\NMr. Masterman.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.32,0:55:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,牙疼的事我很遗憾\NI'm sorry about the toothache.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.08,0:55:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NMerci.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.44,0:55:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢那些小蛋糕\NI love the little cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.76,0:55:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,皮拉尔·艾斯特拉瓦多斯小姐\NSo, Miss Pilar Estravados, you are a missionary...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.36,0:56:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你是名传教士\Nbut you trained as a nurse
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.44,0:56:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但在改行前你曾经做过保姆对吧\Nbefore you changed professions, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.64,0:56:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,是我欠上帝的\NI owed it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.20,0:56:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么说是欠上帝的\NYou owed Him a debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.92,0:56:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经\NThere were...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.24,0:56:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,有过一段非常放纵的生活\Nindulgent times in my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.00,0:56:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,当时的我 索取的太多 给予的太少\Nwhen I took more than I gave.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.76,0:56:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,格哈德哈德曼\NGerhard Hardman.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.20,0:56:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,工程学教授\NProfessor of engineering.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.04,0:56:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,正是因为科学\NIt is science that will win back
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.88,0:56:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,德国才有幸找回了她昔日的光辉\Nfor Germany her pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.76,0:56:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,贝尼亚米诺·马奎兹 - 马奎兹先生\N- Biniamino Marquez. - Mr. Marquez.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.92,0:56:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我不想和\NListen, I wanna be clear
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.20,0:56:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这起案子扯上任何关系\Nof any association with the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.64,0:56:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,有问题尽管问我\Nso please ask me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.92,0:56:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,随便问 我绝不隐瞒\NAnything. I never lie anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.40,0:56:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你昨天有离开过包厢吗\NDid you leave your compartment at all last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.56,0:56:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就离开过一次 去要阿司匹林\NOnly once, to get an aspirin.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.88,0:56:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,哈伯德夫人早先就说过要给我药\NMrs. Hubbard offered me something earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.60,0:56:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,起初我拒绝了 可我实在睡不好\NI declined at first, but when I couldn't rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.72,0:56:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就去找她要了点药\NI went to ask for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.56,0:56:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我的会议将在都灵举行\NMy conference is in Turin.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.96,0:56:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,会议上只有我一个奥地利人\NI am the only Austrian to present,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.92,0:56:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,所以如果我没到场\Nwhich means without me...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.84,0:56:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,会议将延期\Nthe talks will be substandard.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.08,0:56:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我逃出了监狱\NThen I escaped prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.44,0:57:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,搞了个美国身份\Nand I bribed myself into the US...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.24,0:57:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,从此发誓再也不干偷鸡摸狗的事\Nwhere I swore never to lie or steal again.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.84,0:57:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,因为当人们信任你时\NYou see, my friends, because when people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.24,0:57:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,会向你买更多东西\Ntrust you, they buy more.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.80,0:57:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,意大利人就是奶牛 西班牙人就像绵羊\NThe Italians are cows. The Spaniards, sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.60,0:57:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,比利时人吗\NThe Belgians...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.04,0:57:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,当时没发现什么 我回到房间\NI come to my room, which I share
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.80,0:57:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,同屋住的是那个英国管家\Nwith the unhappy English butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.84,0:57:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,像鱼一样 因为总是在嘟哝着什么\NA fish. He groans a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.36,0:57:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但他可以证明我一觉睡到大天亮\NBut I'm sure he saw me sleep all night until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.96,0:57:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,有件事情\NI should say...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.24,0:57:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我想应该和案情有关\Nin case it is relevant...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.00,0:57:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,当我去找哈伯德夫人的时候\Nthere was an embarrassing moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.52,0:57:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,发生了尴尬的一幕\NWhen I went to see Mrs. Hubbard...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.76,0:57:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始我走错房间了\Nfirst, I opened the wrong door.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.44,0:57:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉\NOh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.24,0:57:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,当时是几点\NWhat time was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.60,0:57:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,应该差不多是\NThat must have been about...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.08,0:57:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不用道歉\NDon't be sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.32,0:57:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上十点四十\N...twenty minutes to 11:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.16,0:57:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有意思\NThis is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.32,0:57:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,到现在为止\NAs far as it is known,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.56,0:57:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该是最后一个见到他活着的人\Nyou are the last person to see Ratchett alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.56,0:57:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个商人 卖汽车的\NYour business? Automobiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.28,0:57:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我有三个展厅\NI have three showrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.80,0:57:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,当年我到美国时一穷二白 现在呢\NI come to America with nothing. And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.00,0:58:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我会去向德贝汉小姐求证\NIf what you say is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.12,0:58:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你所说的话\NMiss Debenham will confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.20,0:58:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的全是真的\NBut it is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.28,0:58:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会说谎\NI would not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.32,0:58:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,或许德贝汉小姐\NMay it be possible that Miss Debenham
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.08,0:58:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,离开过你们的包厢 而你没有察觉到\Nleft your compartment without you noticing?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.04,0:58:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我睡得很浅\NNo. I sleep very lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.84,0:58:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,稍稍有点动静 我马上就会惊醒\NThe slightest sound and I bolt upright.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.72,0:58:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经遇到过意外\NI was surprised once.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.40,0:58:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不会再有第二次\NNever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.48,0:58:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我没说我当过专职司机\NNo, I didn't say I was a chauffeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.56,0:58:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你的行李箱掉下来时 照片撒了一地\NThe photographs that spilled out of your luggage...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.12,0:58:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,里面有一张漂亮的照片\Nthere was a beautiful one
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.00,0:58:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,一个小男孩戴着司机的帽子\Nwith a little boy wearing a chauffeur's hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.32,0:58:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,估计是来找正在上班的爸爸\Nvisiting his papa at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.84,0:58:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你给谁当的司机\NWho did you chauffeur?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.68,0:58:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,女士 你手上的老茧很多\NMiss Estravados, why do your hands
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.20,0:58:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,就像拳击手一样\Nhave the calluses of a boxer?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.08,0:58:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我工作的城市大都非常危险\NI do my work in dangerous cities...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.76,0:58:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,为了让自己不生活在恐惧当中\Nwhere I cannot be governed by fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.52,0:58:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我接受过搏击训练\NI trained to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.68,0:58:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,经历那次意外之后\NBut you do not trust your god anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.44,0:58:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你连上帝也不信了?\Nsince your surprise?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.04,0:58:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不 以防他忙不过来\NNo, in case He is busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.04,0:58:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝一直都很忙\NGod is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.60,0:58:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是马斯特曼\NIt's Masterman.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.08,0:59:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一个将死之人没什么可顾忌的了\NA man dying is a man with nothing to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.84,0:59:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 布克 但有个问题\NBravo, Bouc. Except for the problem of Mr. Marquez...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.00,0:59:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,马奎兹先生已经证实了\Nwho has now confirmed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.08,0:59:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他的室友马斯特曼先生在案发当时\Nthat his bunkmate, Masterman...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.40,0:59:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,正在床上看书\Nwas reading in his bed at the time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.44,0:59:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,真这么简单我就不会出名了 下一个\NIf it were easy, I would not be famous. Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.44,0:59:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,德贝汉小姐\NMiss Debenham...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.60,0:59:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你不介意出来透透气吧\Nyou do not mind to brace the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.40,0:59:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,为你 我们准备了野餐\NFor you, we have the picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.28,0:59:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,询问我室友时选在了狭隘的地方\NWhile you made my roommate suffer cramped quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.80,0:59:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂了\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.08,0:59:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不同对象\NChoose the best location
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.20,0:59:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,选择在不同地点询问他们\Nto extract the truth from each suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.92,0:59:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,让她措不及防 让我来受冻\NPut her off-balance and me, freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.24,0:59:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你很聪明\NClever.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.40,0:59:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,请写下你的全名和\NWill you write down your full name
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.68,0:59:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,地址好吗\Nand address, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.52,0:59:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,对了 是淡紫色\NA pale mauve, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.36,0:59:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,艾斯特拉瓦多斯小姐说你问了\NMiss Estravados told me you asked
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.76,0:59:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,她睡袍的颜色\Nthe color of her dressing gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.20,0:59:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NMerci.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.72,0:59:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,玛丽·赫尔迈厄尼·德贝汉\N"Mary Hermione Debenham."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.56,0:59:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,有人会叫你赫尔迈厄尼吗\NDo you ever go by Hermione?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.92,0:59:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,除了工作时大家都叫我玛丽\NA constant Mary, when I'm not employed as Miss Debenham.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.96,0:59:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,左撇子\NLeft-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.92,1:00:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,很罕见 我知道\NUnusual, I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.36,1:00:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你还在研究笔迹\NYou mustn't have your theory fixed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.56,1:00:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那就证明你还没有结论\Nif you're testing my handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.40,1:00:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么看死者\NWhat did you think of the dead man?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.92,1:00:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我基本上没怎么注意他\NUh, I can't say I did think about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.52,1:00:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我不懂这个问题的意义何在\NI don't quite see the point of your question.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.96,1:00:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,原谅我 小姐 这是我的一个小诀窍\NOh, forgive me, mademoiselle, my little originalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.44,1:00:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,人性多变而且复杂\NHuman nature is perverse in its complexity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.04,1:00:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,所以想要抽丝剥茧 就得用对工具\NTo plumb it, it takes the right tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.04,1:00:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你这是把戏不是工具 赫尔克里\NThese are toys, not tools, Hercule.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.20,1:00:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你更直接些\NI prefer you put them away.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.56,1:00:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,更直接吗 很好\NThe direct method? Parfait.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.36,1:00:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你和医生之前就认识吧\NYou knew the doctor before traveling?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.76,1:00:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯诺特医生\NDr. Arbuthnot?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.56,1:00:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.16,1:00:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,所以是一见钟情\NBut such instant attraction?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.60,1:00:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这里不是美国\NWe are not in America...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.12,1:00:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,德贝汉小姐 这里没有法律\NMiss Debenham. There are no laws
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.56,1:00:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,会制约你的感情\Nagainst what you may feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.16,1:00:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,同时也没有哪条法律不允许我缄默\NNor are there laws against silence, of which...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.48,1:00:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我\NI hold my...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.52,1:01:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没去过美国\NI've never been to America.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.68,1:01:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我还想问你 关于我无意中\NPerhaps I may ask about some...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.96,1:01:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,听到的几句话\Nwords I overheard?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.32,1:01:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你和阿巴斯诺特似乎\NYou and the stranger, Arbuthnot,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.24,1:01:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,要比一般陌生人来得更亲近些\Nare closer than strangers might be.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.52,1:01:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我听你说\NYou said...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.68,1:01:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不是现在 事成之后 就没人能阻碍我们了\N"Not now. When we are done. Then no one can touch us."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.12,1:01:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思\NWhat did you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.20,1:01:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为我说的谋杀?\NYou think I meant murder?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.08,1:01:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,拿着锤子的人眼里到处都是钉子\NTo a man with a hammer, every problem is a nail.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.08,1:01:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你看多了罪犯\NYou live crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.88,1:01:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,就觉得所有人都是魔鬼 - 正相反\NYou see evil every day. Not so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.20,1:01:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我看多了罪犯\NI see enough crime to know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.76,1:01:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我知道哪些地方不寻常\Nthat the criminal act is the anomaly.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.88,1:01:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信一个人如果杀了另一个人\NI believe it takes a fracture of the soul...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.28,1:01:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他的灵魂就不会再完整\Nto murder another human being.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.12,1:01:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我再问一遍 那话到底什么意思\NI ask again, what did you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.36,1:01:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,正如我刚才说的\NAs we established...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.48,1:01:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,没有哪条法律要求我一定要开口\Nthere are no laws against my silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.16,1:01:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\NVery well.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.56,1:02:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,接下来是德拉戈米罗夫公主\NAnd afterwards, Princess Dragomiroff?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.40,1:02:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,吃完晚餐 我就去睡了\NAfter dinner, I came to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.84,1:02:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝让我长寿\NGod blessed me with long life,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.60,1:02:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但却让我受到背痛的困扰 让我痛苦不已\Nbut cursed me with a bad back to make it miserable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.68,1:02:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,大概是十二点三刻\NAbout a quarter to 1:00...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.40,1:02:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫来了施密特小姐\NI called for Fräulein Schmidt.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.92,1:02:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,让她给我做按摩\NMmm-hmm. She massaged me...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.64,1:02:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,给我念了会书\Nand read to me for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.96,1:02:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,之后我就睡着了\N- Then I sleep. - Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.32,1:02:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,您认不认识\NWere you ever acquainted...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.72,1:02:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗一家人\Nwith a family by the name of Armstrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.52,1:02:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他们遭遇了惨绝人寰的悲剧\NThey endured an unspeakable tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.16,1:02:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我很欣赏索尼娅·阿姆斯特朗的母亲\NI was an admirer of Sonia Armstrong's mother...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.76,1:02:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,琳达·雅顿  她是个演员\NLinda Arden, the actress.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.12,1:02:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,百年一遇的奇才\NA once-a-century talent.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.12,1:03:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,雅顿小姐当时想转做导演\NMiss Arden was to turn to directing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.92,1:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,要不是那场悲剧\NShe would have become the first
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.80,1:03:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我想她早就成为了\Nwoman titan of Broadway...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.28,1:03:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,百老汇第一位女巨人\Nwere it not for the tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.36,1:03:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,那么这位琳达·雅顿死了吗\NAnd this Linda Arden, she is dead?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.16,1:03:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,还不如死了呢\NShe might as well be.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.96,1:03:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,从此以后 她足不出户\NShe no longer leaves her home.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.04,1:03:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,黛西 是我的教女\NDaisy was my goddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.88,1:03:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,她是个\NShe was a...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.28,1:03:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白这和这起案子有什么关系\NI don't see how this relates to our troubles, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.60,1:03:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,昨晚的受害人 他的真名叫做卡萨蒂\NThe man killed last night, his true name was Cassetti.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.36,1:03:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,杀死小黛西·阿姆斯特朗的凶手\NThe man who murdered little Daisy Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.76,1:03:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂了\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.52,1:03:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我确实认识这家人 现在那家伙却死了\NI admit I know this family, and now this man is dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.64,1:03:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这么巧合\NThe coincidence...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.92,1:04:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,实在说不过去\Nmust seem unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.00,1:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,或许 这确实只是个巧合\NYou may be permitted a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.84,1:04:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不过现在 我有一些问题要问这位施密特小姐\NI must now ask a few questions of your Fräulein Schmidt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.08,1:04:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,不 没这个必要\NNo. There is no need.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.48,1:04:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以为她的人格作担保\NI can answer to her character.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.20,1:04:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,既然如此 如果您允许的话\NEven still, if you will allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.80,1:04:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,小姐 请用德语回答\NFraulein. Answer please in German.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.92,1:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这样公主殿下就听不懂我说的了\NBut her Excellency cannot comprehend me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.84,1:04:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,目的就是这个\NThat is the point.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.48,1:04:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你的吗  H指的是你的名字希尔德加德\NThis is yours? H for Hildegarde?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.44,1:04:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我用不起这么高级的东西\NIt is too fine for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.28,1:04:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,关于昨晚的事  她说的是实话吗\NThis is the truth about last night?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.36,1:04:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,正如她所说的 她让列车员把我叫来\NAs she said. She sent the conductor for me,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.20,1:04:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我就回去睡觉了\Nthen I returned to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.08,1:04:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你回去的时候有看到谁吗\NDid you see anyone when you returned?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.00,1:04:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,只看到了另一名列车员\NOnly the other conductor.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.96,1:04:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,另一名列车员\N"The other conductor."
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.08,1:04:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,是指米歇尔吗\NYou mean Michel?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.00,1:04:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不是那个叫醒我的人\NNo. A different one than had awoken me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.84,1:04:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,请跟我来\NPlease come with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.20,1:05:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定不是他吗\NAre you sure you did not see him?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.52,1:05:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我确定 另一个\NI'm certain. The other conductor
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.64,1:05:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,身材矮小 留着短胡子\Nwas a small man with a short beard.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.88,1:05:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,小姐 这儿只有一名列车员\NFräulein, there is no other conductor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.12,1:05:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我看的很清楚\NI know what I saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.28,1:05:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得他的声音很尖\NI remember because his voice was high
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.72,1:05:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,穿着同样的制服\Nand the uniform was the same exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.04,1:05:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜上面还少了一颗纽扣\NThough, I suspect, missing one button.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.92,1:05:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我急需你的总钥匙\NSir, I need your passkey immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.64,1:05:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要找一件制服和一件红色的和式睡袍\NWe need to find a uniform and a red kimono.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.64,1:05:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,只找到几千张照片\NThousands of photographs,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.12,1:05:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,无数双袜子\Nendless pairs of socks...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.28,1:05:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,五颜六色的睡袍 就是没有红色的\Ndressing gowns in every color but red...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.28,1:05:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,也没找到列车员的制服\Nand still no contraband conductor's uniform.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.28,1:05:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,所有乘客的行李箱都查过了吗\NHave we checked all the passengers' luggage?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.88,1:05:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,除了安德烈伯爵\NAll except for the Count
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.24,1:05:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,和他夫人的行李还没查\Nand Countess Andrenyi, monsieur.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.64,1:05:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我们无权搜查他们的行李箱\NIt is forbidden to search their suitcases.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.76,1:05:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他们持有外交签证\NThey travel under diplomatic visas.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.72,1:05:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,那还会去哪儿呢\NWhere else could it be?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.76,1:05:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,还有一个人的行李箱没有查过\NThere is one last suitcase we have not checked.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.28,1:05:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我自己的\NMy own.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.08,1:05:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手是在嘲笑我\NThe killer is mocking me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.48,1:05:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 这是他犯的第一个错误\NGood. His first mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.40,1:05:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那么有些事我自然也猜到了\NAnd as the night must follow the day...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.60,1:05:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉小姐\NPardon, mademoiselle.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.40,1:05:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不 这不是我的\NNo, it's not mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.96,1:06:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,如果真是我的\NI told you of the conductor. Why would I tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.76,1:06:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我为什么要告诉你呢\Nif it was me? You would not...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.00,1:06:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,确实如此 所以你的包厢是最安全的地方\Nwhich makes your compartment the ideal choice to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.28,1:06:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,少了颗纽扣\NVoilà, the button.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.72,1:06:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,如果这个人能够找到列车员的制服\NAnd if a conductor's uniform...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.52,1:06:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他又怎么可能找不到列车员的钥匙呢\Nwhy not a conductor's passkey?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.76,1:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们知道凶手\NNow we know how the killer
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.12,1:06:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,是如何打开上了锁的门了\Nmagically passed through locked doors.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.88,1:06:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,波旁酒的味道 - 麦奎因\NBourbon. MacQueen.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.80,1:06:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,要找什么\NNow what are we looking for now?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.92,1:06:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,500英镑\N500 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.32,1:06:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,麦奎因也有个账本\NMacQueen also had a ledger.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.56,1:06:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,记录了他和雷切特的所有生意\NAll his dealings with Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.08,1:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,在哪\NWhere is it, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.20,1:06:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛\NPoirot?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.68,1:06:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,布克 让大家都别出来\NBouc, keep everyone inside!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.20,1:06:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,先生 请站住\NMonsieur! Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.24,1:06:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,先生\NMonsieur!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.72,1:07:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,先生\NMonsieur!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.04,1:07:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,请站着别动\NPlease stay where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.04,1:07:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 先生们 多谢\NThank you, gentlemen. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.60,1:07:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 是麦奎因干的 凶手抓到了\NSo, it was MacQueen? You have your man?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.64,1:07:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思 女士\NPardonnez-moi, madame.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.32,1:07:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么会是他\NHow could he?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.40,1:07:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我没杀他\NI didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.56,1:07:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你企图烧掉账本\NYou tried to burn Ratchett's accounts...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.84,1:07:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,可有些地方还是看得出来\Nbut they are still legible in places.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.16,1:07:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,数字根本对不上\NThe maths do not tally...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.32,1:07:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你偷了他的钱\Nbecause you have been stealing from him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.08,1:08:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这简直就是\NIt is full of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.76,1:08:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-  英语里面要怎么说 - 就是指很混乱\N- What is the English word? - The chocolat?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.16,1:08:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,糊涂账\NFudge? Fudge!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.28,1:08:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,一笔糊涂账\NIt is full of the fudge!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.64,1:08:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你偷了他的钱\NYou stole from him!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.64,1:08:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你怕他会发现\NYou thought you would be found out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.36,1:08:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你就杀了他\NThat is why you killed him!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.68,1:08:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,对\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.84,1:08:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你说得对 我是偷了他的钱\NYeah, you're damn right I stole from him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.44,1:08:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,好几千块\NThousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.76,1:08:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道他的钱不干净\NI knew his money wasn't honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.64,1:08:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,既然这样我揩点油又有什么关系\NWhat did it matter if I skimmed some off the top?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.08,1:08:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我倒想问你一个问题\NBut let me ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.16,1:08:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我为什么要做杀鸡取卵的事情\NWhy would I slaughter my cash cow?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.08,1:08:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,不是我干的\NI didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.48,1:08:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我没杀他 - 不是他\N- I didn't kill him! - He didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.92,1:08:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不是他\NHe didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.00,1:08:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以做他的不在场证明\NI expect his alibi revolves around me,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.80,1:08:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我们凌晨时在喝酒\Ndrinking till the early hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.12,1:08:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是真的\NWell, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.28,1:08:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我看他在喝威士忌\NI saw him having whiskey, and remarked
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.08,1:08:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,然后就说美国酒不如英国的好\Non the lesser quality of American liquor.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.12,1:08:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他想让我改观\NHe offered me a tipple
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.20,1:08:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就请我喝了几杯\Nto change my mind, then another.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.32,1:08:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们当时探讨了政治话题\NWe got to arguing politics. He had some...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.96,1:08:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我不太赞同他对斯大林的一些看法\Ntomfool opinions on Stalin
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.60,1:08:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但对于酒他确实很在行\NI had to correct. But the man knows his spirits.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.56,1:09:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,借一步说话 先生\NA word, please, monsieur.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.64,1:09:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定你们整晚都在一起吗\NYou can confirm you were with him all night?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.68,1:09:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们抽烟聊天到将近两点\NWe smoked and spoke till nearly 2:00, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.92,1:09:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你们俩还真是投缘 他抽的是烟\NAh, such chums, him with his cigarettes, and you...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.88,1:09:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得你是这车上唯一抽烟斗的人\NYes, you are the only man on the train who smokes a pipe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.44,1:09:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,能看一下你的烟斗和烟丝吗\NMay I see your pipe and your tobacco, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.56,1:09:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.72,1:09:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯诺特医生\NAnd you, Dr. Arbuthnot,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.84,1:09:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你是从印度出发的对吧\Nwere traveling from India, I believe. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.56,1:09:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,现在开始审问我了吧\NYou're interviewing me now? Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.56,1:09:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在雷切特被杀前你去过他的包厢吗\NWere you ever in Ratchett's compartment
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.76,1:09:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,当然没有\Nbefore he was killed? Certainly not.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.68,1:09:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这可是你的烟斗通条不是吗\NBut this is one of your pipe cleaners, n'est-ce pas?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.80,1:09:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是在死者的包厢里找到的 劝你再找仔细点\NIf you found that in the dead man's cabin, look elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.60,1:09:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我是名医生\NI am a doctor, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.92,1:09:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我只会救人不会害人\NI heal people. I do not hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.44,1:09:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,说到这点 你一定非常努力\NAbout this, see, you must have worked
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.16,1:09:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,才能当上医生\Nvery hard to become a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.76,1:09:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,很少有非洲裔的朋友有机会当上医生\NNot many of your race are allowed the opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.28,1:09:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,米德尔塞克斯医学院每个班只招一个黑人\NMiddlesex Medical College permits one per class.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.36,1:09:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我1924年入的学\NI had the honor in '24.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.76,1:09:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我服役时是一名狙击手\NI was a sniper in my tour.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.44,1:09:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,射的很准\NA sharpshooter.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.20,1:09:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我救了不少军官\NSaved more than a few officers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.76,1:09:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,其中有人心存感激\NThe more grateful,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.80,1:09:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,赏识我头脑冷静 双手稳健\Nrecognized a fair mind with a steady hand...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.44,1:09:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,资助我完成了学业\Nand supported my education.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.44,1:10:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我从此欠下了人情\NI take their generosity as a debt.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.00,1:10:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,认识阿姆斯特朗上校吗\NDid you know a Colonel Armstrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.32,1:10:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,有两三个姓阿姆斯特朗的\NMight have known two or three Armstrongs.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.44,1:10:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,第60步兵团有个汤米·阿姆斯特朗\NTommy in the 60th... Selby Armstrong...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.20,1:10:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我说的是约翰·阿姆斯特朗\NNo, I meant Colonel John Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.80,1:10:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他娶了个美国妻子\NHe had an American wife,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.12,1:10:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,而他的孩子被绑匪撕票了\Nand his child was kidnapped and killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.52,1:10:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认识他\NNever came across the fellow.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.68,1:10:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次见德贝汉小姐是什么时候\NWhen did you first meet Miss Debenham?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.96,1:10:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我们第一次见面是在护卫车上\NWe met when we shared the railway convoy car
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.88,1:10:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,从基尔库克到尼西宾\Nfrom Kirkuk to Nissibin.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.20,1:10:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,她可不是这么说的\NShe claims otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.36,1:10:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这点让她变得非常可疑\Nand she has made herself problematically suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.64,1:10:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 失陪了\NExcusez-moi.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.80,1:10:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,玛丽是个好人\NMary is a lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.32,1:10:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,别把她扯进来 我可以为她的人格担保\NLeave her out of this. I can vouch for her character.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.16,1:10:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你担保麦奎因的不在场证明一样吗\NAs you vouched for MacQueen's time?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.52,1:10:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你根本不听别人说什么 没错\NYou won't listen to reason. Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.00,1:10:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,算你走运 好心的医生说\NYou are lucky. The good doctor insists
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.84,1:10:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他一直跟你在一起\Nhe did not let you out of his sight.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.72,1:10:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,看吧 所以不可能是我\NSee? There. Couldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.40,1:10:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,当然有可能\NYes, you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.68,1:10:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特每晚都会服用安眠药\NRatchett took a sleeping draught each evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.68,1:10:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以轻易的混入镇定剂\NYou could add barbital, easily access that drug.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.68,1:10:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,再给医生的酒杯里也放点\NDo the same with one of the doctor's many drinks...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.72,1:10:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这样你就有机会杀人了\Nand the chance to kill him is clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.24,1:10:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我为什么要那么做\NWhy would I do any of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.44,1:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,动机刚才已经分析过了\NWe have established your motive.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.68,1:11:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,或许还有别的动机\NPerhaps I will suggest a different one.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.84,1:11:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,还有内情 可能是出于更私人的原因\NA different reason, a more personal reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.40,1:11:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,学法律出身 可惜却不是这块料\N"A lawyer by education, not by disposition."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.40,1:11:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我很好奇你为什么学法律\NWhy did you pursue the law, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.60,1:11:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,是不是为了应付\NWas it to appease a much loved,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.20,1:11:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你敬爱而又严厉的父亲\Nbut demanding father...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.48,1:11:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他曾经是那么的成功\None who himself had made a great success
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.72,1:11:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,同样是在法律界\Nin the same field...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.24,1:11:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,不过后来 他失势了\Nand then lost his position?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.36,1:11:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经有一个大名鼎鼎的麦奎因 不是吗\NThere was a renowned MacQueen, was there not?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.68,1:11:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他是新泽西州的一名地方检察官\NThe district attorney for the state of New Jersey...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.40,1:11:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是当年\Nresponsible for the prosecution
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.52,1:11:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗案的公诉人\Nof the Armstrong case.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.60,1:11:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他们找不到嫌疑犯\NThey didn't have a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.00,1:11:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我爸爸被迫将矛头指向了\NMy dad was pressured to go after
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.04,1:11:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,那个可怜的法国女人\Nthis poor French woman...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.08,1:11:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,那个女佣没有有力的不在场证明 苏珊\Na maid with a weak alibi, Susanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.84,1:12:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,他把罪责归咎于她\NHe hung his whole case on her.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.24,1:12:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,然后她自杀了\NShe killed herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.36,1:12:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,她是无辜的\NShe was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.20,1:12:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,后来有证据显示凶手是卡萨蒂\NBy the time the evidence lead to Cassetti,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.52,1:12:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,可他早跑了\Noh, he was long gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.08,1:12:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我父亲成了众矢之的\NThey tore my old man apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.24,1:12:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,可我却帮不了他\NI couldn't do anything for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.44,1:12:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,即便是这样\NAnd yet you claim
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.76,1:12:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你还说不知道雷切特就是卡萨蒂\Nthat you did not know Ratchett was Cassetti?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.92,1:12:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不  不\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.72,1:12:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,可你还是找到了他\NBut you found him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.04,1:12:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.08,1:12:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你找到了他\NYou found him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.24,1:12:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,卷走了他的钱\NYou bled him dry... No.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.32,1:12:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好还清你父亲欠下的债\Nin order to settle your father's debts,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.76,1:12:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,于是到了最后 替你父亲报了仇\Nand then finally, to settle the score.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.08,1:12:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有\NNo, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.56,1:12:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,不是这样的\NNo. It wasn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.64,1:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我只不过是\NIt wasn't like that. It's not the way...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.92,1:12:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,有人闯了进来\NSomeone kicked in the door...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.12,1:12:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,医生\NDoctor!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.40,1:12:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,捂住了我的脸\Ncovered my face.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.76,1:12:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,先得把刀拔出来\NAll right, this needs to come out now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.48,1:13:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,拿我的包来  好的\NI want my bag. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.48,1:13:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的包厢里\NIt's in my compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.52,1:13:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,上面不会有指纹\NThere will be no fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.80,1:13:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手想把凶器处理掉\NThe killer was disposing of the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.96,1:13:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就在那儿\NIt's there!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.24,1:13:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,幸好没伤到肺和动脉\NThe killer didn't hit a lung or artery.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.28,1:13:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,能活着算走运了\NShe's lucky to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.92,1:13:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都很走运\NYou all are.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.44,1:13:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的大侦探\NYeah, some genius!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.60,1:13:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么还没有破案\NWhy haven't you solved this case?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.48,1:13:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你得给他一点时间\NYou must give the man some time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.60,1:13:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,行了\NYeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.96,1:13:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,再给他时间我的血都要流干了\NI can't give that much more. I don't have any blood left.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.16,1:13:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,拉着麦奎因谈话\NAccosting Mr. MacQueen,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.48,1:13:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,结果真凶却在这儿\Nand the real killer is right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.16,1:13:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你们中的一个\NOne of you people.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.28,1:13:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道那人是谁 我什么也没说\NI don't know who you are. I said nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.00,1:13:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,求你 放过我吧\NPlease, leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.60,1:13:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,放点音乐\NPlay something.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.16,1:13:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,各位 铁轨明早就能清理好\NMy friends, the tracks will be cleared by morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.36,1:13:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,请回房休息吧\NPlease, return to your rooms.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.08,1:13:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我就睡在这儿\NI'm sleeping here...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.28,1:13:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都看得到我 我也看得到你们\Nwhere everyone can see me and I can see everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.64,1:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都该如此\NYou should all do the same. Conserve heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.36,1:14:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,明早之前最好待在明处 彼此有个照应\NRemain in the open, safely in view, until morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.28,1:14:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手能杀一个就能杀第二个\NA killer will never hesitate to kill again.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.40,1:14:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这话我也会对安德烈伯爵夫妇说\NI will convey the same message to the Andrenyis...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.64,1:14:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不管他们有没有外交豁免权\Ndiplomatic immunity or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.04,1:14:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果可以的话 我想看一下你们的护照\NIf I may, I will look at your passports.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.16,1:14:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须得找她谈谈\NYou know that I must talk with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.40,1:14:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你妻子的名字上有一块污渍\NBy the way, there is a grease spot on your wife's name.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.20,1:14:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能得看一下\NYou might want to look at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.40,1:14:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,埃琳娜她不舒服\NElena is not well.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.00,1:14:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,如果您不配合\NIf you do not permit me, your reluctance
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.56,1:14:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我会把情况报告给南斯拉夫警方\Nwill be noted to the Yugoslav Police...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.76,1:14:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,相信他们一定会逮捕你们\Nand I have no doubt that they will arrest both you and...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.24,1:14:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你竟敢口出狂言\NHow dare you!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.28,1:14:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的\NDarling!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.08,1:14:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的\NDarling.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.40,1:14:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你的样子很滑稽 波洛先生\NYou are funny-looking, monsieur Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.40,1:14:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,每个侦探都长得这么滑稽吗\NAre all detectives so funny-looking?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.40,1:15:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 吵醒你了 伯爵夫人\NI am sorry to wake you, Madame la Comtesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.28,1:15:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我晚上一般都醒着\NI am always awake at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.40,1:15:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,白天用来睡觉\NIn the day, I sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.48,1:15:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,有人害怕黑夜 而我却受不了阳光\NSome fear darkness, but I cannot stand the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.76,1:15:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,请问你是不是一直都在使用\NYou are always under the influence of...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.60,1:15:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,巴比妥\NBarbital.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.28,1:15:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,巴比妥 巴比妥\NBarbital, barbital.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.60,1:15:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,大概都用了一卡车了吧\NI take oceans of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.32,1:15:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,说谎是没用的 亲爱的\NOh, there's no use in a lie, love.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.56,1:15:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他一眼就能看穿我们\NHe can see right through us.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.56,1:15:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,没有它 我根本出不了门\NI cannot go outside without it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.08,1:15:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,没有它 我连觉都睡不着\NI cannot sleep without it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.12,1:15:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我用它来克服恐惧\NI take it against my fears.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.76,1:15:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你在害怕什么\NWhat are you afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.28,1:15:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这一切\NEverything.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.24,1:15:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你护照上写着 你娘家的姓氏是戈登伯格\NYour passport has your maiden name as Goldenberg.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.08,1:16:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,犹太人对吗\NJewish, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.60,1:16:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,血统并不纯正 我的中间名是玛利亚\NNot so Jewish. My middle name isn't Maria.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.32,1:16:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你和你丈夫都是舞者吗\NAnd you are a dancer like your husband?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.20,1:16:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不 他和我不一样\NNo, not like my husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.28,1:16:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我是芭蕾舞团的伴舞\NCorps de ballet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.48,1:16:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他是天生的舞蹈家\NHe is touched by angels.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.76,1:16:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,而我只是一个靠\NI have been shoved by passion
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.76,1:16:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,热情和磨练才勉强够格的人\Nand hard work to become adequate.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.96,1:16:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我得回去躺着了\NExcuse me, I must lie down again.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.44,1:16:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这是您唯一一件睡袍吗\NIs this your only dressing gown?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.84,1:16:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有另一条 黄色的雪纺\NNo, I have another. Corn-colored chiffon.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.16,1:16:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢和侦探聊天\NI like speaking to detectives.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.80,1:16:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你永远猜不到他们接下来会问什么\NYou never know what they're going to ask you next.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.96,1:16:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道很多国家的首都\NI'm particularly good at capitals.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.36,1:16:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我的家庭教师教授地理课时非常严格\NMy governess was a stickler for geography.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.16,1:16:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你满意了吧\NAre you satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.08,1:16:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,确实如此 因为我看穿了一个谎言\NI am always satisfied when I uncover a liar.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.36,1:16:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,女士 你的名字不叫埃琳娜 应该是海伦娜\NMadame, your name is not Elena. It is Helena.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.16,1:16:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管你们在护照和行李牌上\NDespite your clumsy attempts
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.36,1:16:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,都动了手脚\Nto change it here and on your luggage.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.24,1:17:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我丈夫听说\NMy husband heard
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.48,1:17:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你们找到一样证物\Nof a piece of evidence found...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.16,1:17:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,一块绣了H字母的手帕\Na handkerchief embroidered with an "H,"
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.88,1:17:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他不想让我牵扯其中\Nand didn't want my "H" involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.36,1:17:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们改了它 行李牌还有护照\NSo we changed it. The luggage and the passport.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.00,1:17:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,远离是非应该算不上犯罪吧\NIt's no crime to want to be distant from trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.52,1:17:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但是非就在眼前\NYet, here is trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.40,1:17:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这起案子\NA curious detail
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.72,1:17:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,一直围绕着阿姆斯特朗惨案\Nabout the Armstrong tragedy at the heart of this case...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.40,1:17:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但令人费解的是 究竟有多少人 因此受到了伤害\Nis how many people were wounded by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.08,1:17:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,一个是受害者的妹妹\NThe younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.04,1:17:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,另一个是作为演员的母亲\NThe actress mother...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.12,1:17:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,艺名叫做琳达·雅顿\Nstage name, Linda Arden.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.52,1:17:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜她应该也有犹太血统 犹太演员\NI suppose she, too, was of Jewish ancestry...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.40,1:17:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,通常不都会取艺名吗\Nas who is most likely to take a stage name?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.08,1:17:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,所以是不是可以大胆地猜测\NIs it too far to suggest...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.20,1:17:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,她的本名正是戈登伯格\Nher original name was Goldenberg?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.40,1:17:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,尤其当我看到眼前的这位年轻姑娘\NEspecially when we find a young woman,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.44,1:17:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,她和演员的女儿\Nthe same age...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.08,1:17:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,年纪相仿\Nas her surviving daughter...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.04,1:17:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,整天生活在恐惧之中\Nliving in a world of fear?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.96,1:17:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,她就是索尼娅的妹妹\NThe sister of Sonia Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.92,1:18:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,滚出去\NGet out!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.72,1:18:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我听到了声音 就赶来了 没来晚吧\NI hear noises and I run. Just in time, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.40,1:18:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,现在你该相信了吧 伯爵夫妇就是凶手\NYou must now believe the count and countess are the killers.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.44,1:18:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,伯爵只是保护欲过强\NThe count is protective.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.48,1:18:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他夫人连打死只蜘蛛都不敢\NThe countess would no sooner kill a bedroom spider.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.28,1:18:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你不必装了\NAnd you may desist with this charade.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.28,1:18:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你不是奥地利人 不是德国人 也不是教授\NYou are neither an Austrian, nor a German, nor a professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.28,1:18:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但你学得很像\NBut a good imitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.12,1:18:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,是模仿你认识的某个人吗\NWas it based on someone you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.64,1:18:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我老家有个屠夫是个德国佬\NA local butcher where I grew up was a Kraut.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.72,1:18:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,人很好 口音纯正\NGood man, great accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.20,1:18:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么看出来的\NWhat was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.64,1:18:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你说“都灵”的时候\NYou said "Tur-in..."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.52,1:18:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,重音放错了地方\Nthe emphasis on the wrong syllable
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.48,1:18:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,骄傲而又严谨的日耳曼人是不会\Nfor a proud and proper Teuton.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.72,1:18:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,读错重音的\N"Tu-reen."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.56,1:18:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是太敏锐了 我算是服了\NYou are one sharp knife, I give you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.48,1:19:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,奥地利教授 格哈德·哈德曼\NHerr Professor Gerhard Hardman...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.32,1:19:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,是个假身份\Nis my cover.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.40,1:19:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉上演了一出种族歧视的戏码\NI'm sorry about the colored folks cracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.00,1:19:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,其实我自己也算半个犹太人\NHell, I'm half a Heeb myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.16,1:19:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,塞勒斯·贝斯曼·哈德曼\NCyrus Bethman Hardman.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.00,1:19:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你是私家侦探\NYou are a Pinkerton detective?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.52,1:19:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,做了三十年了\N30 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.60,1:19:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我在伊斯坦布尔 刚刚结束工作\NI was in Stamboul, coming back from a job,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.60,1:19:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,公司就发电报给我\Nwhen the office cabled.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.72,1:19:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,说雷切特想找个人保护他\NRatchett asked for a man to tail him,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.52,1:19:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,出三倍价钱\Noffering triple time.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.84,1:19:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,正好我就在附近\NLucky me being nearby.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.40,1:19:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他告诉我说\NHe told me to look out
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.52,1:19:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,要我留意一个矮个子尖嗓音的黑人\Nfor a small, dark man with a high voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.92,1:19:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我从我的门缝里\NI watched that hall...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.56,1:19:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,盯着那条走廊整整一个晚上\Nall night through a crack in my door.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.60,1:19:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,如果凶手出现的话\NAny thug...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.88,1:19:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,也会先经过我这里\Nhad to go by me first.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.64,1:19:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我发誓是真的\NI'll take my oath on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.08,1:19:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,那你是不是也能发誓\NAnd would you also take your oath...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.48,1:20:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,自己真的做了三十年的私家侦探\Non your thirty years as a Pinkerton Detective...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.20,1:20:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,还是你又想骗我\Nor would you lie to me again...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.92,1:20:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,否认自己曾经是一名警察的事实\Nand deny that you were, in fact, a policeman first?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.60,1:20:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你的枪 枪托上的格纹 蓝色的漆面\NYour gun, the checkered grip, the blue finish...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.24,1:20:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,显然是特制的警用左轮手枪\Nproduced for the Police Positive edition.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.44,1:20:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,1927年投入使用\N1927 issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.24,1:20:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,看来你准备了一箩筐\NIt appears there are no end to the lies
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.88,1:20:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,专门为我设计的谎言\Nmanufactured just for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.32,1:20:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,放下枪 你可以走了 教授\NYou can leave your gun as you go, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.24,1:20:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,从他包厢的位置\NFrom the position of his cabin...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.80,1:20:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不可能看不到凶手\Nit would have been impossible to miss.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.16,1:20:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,除非雷切特的门当时是开着的\NUnless Ratchett's door was open...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.04,1:21:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,就像皮拉尔说的 她误打开过那扇门\Nas Pilar Estravados claims she opened it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.12,1:21:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那样的话凶手就可能\NIn which case, someone could have been...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.60,1:21:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,逃过他的视线\Nmasked from his view.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.00,1:21:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我亲爱的凯瑟琳\NMy darling Katherine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.04,1:21:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一起非常棘手的案子\NThis is an abominable crime...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.80,1:21:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,而我却陷入了困境\Nand I am stuck, ma Katherine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.00,1:21:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我找不到墙上的裂缝\NI cannot find the crack in the wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.80,1:21:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他们中有人迷惑了我\NWhy does one of them elude me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.68,1:21:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,一直以来我都\NI have always been...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.52,1:21:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,非常自信\Nso sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.48,1:21:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,太自信了\NToo sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.48,1:21:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,而现在的我\NBut now, I am very humble.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.16,1:21:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,就像一个孩子 谦卑的说\NAnd I say, like a little child...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.20,1:21:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的想不明白\NI do not know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.24,1:22:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我很怕 凯瑟琳\NI am afraid, ma Katherine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.48,1:22:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉 女士们先生们\NMy apologies, ladies and gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.04,1:22:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,列出重回轨道时\NIt is not safe on board
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.36,1:22:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,待在车厢里会有危险\Nwhilst the engine is put back on the tracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.12,1:22:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去隧道里等候 谢谢\NWe are to wait in the tunnel. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.72,1:22:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要把狗带去哪儿\NWhere are they taking the dogs?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.12,1:22:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,它们会高兴的\NThey'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.48,1:22:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这可不行\NThat's not right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.64,1:22:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,活动活动挺好的\NJust to stretch their legs, it's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.28,1:22:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不  这么做不对\NNo, that's not right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.40,1:22:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,冻死了\NIt's freezing!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.36,1:22:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你找我\NYou asked for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.64,1:22:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,又要审问了么\NAnother interrogation?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.92,1:22:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我喜欢和你聊天\NOh, no. I enjoy your company.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.56,1:22:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 布克\NMerci, Bouc.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.00,1:22:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,请坐\NUh, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.76,1:22:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我列出了十个问题 还没找到答案\NI have a list of ten questions I am no nearer to answering...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.52,1:22:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但火车马上要开了\Nand the train is about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.60,1:22:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你头脑敏锐\NYou have a clear mind...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.96,1:22:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,说不准你会想到什么 请看\Nand I thought that you might produce an insight. Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.28,1:23:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,手帕 烟斗通条\N"The handkerchief. The pipe cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.52,1:23:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,红色睡袍 制服\N"The scarlet kimono. The uniform.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.36,1:23:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,手表上的时间\N"The time on the watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.72,1:23:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,案发的时间 是之前还是之后\N"Was he murdered then? Earlier or later?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.76,1:23:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,一人还是多人作案\N"By one person or more?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.32,1:23:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,哪几位\N"Which of them?"
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.08,1:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我帮不了你\NSorry, I can't help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.96,1:23:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NUh... Merci.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.16,1:23:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,或许还有第十一个问题\NPerhaps there is an eleventh question
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.56,1:23:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你没想到\Nyou don't know to ask yet...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.04,1:23:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,它能解决其他所有问题\Nthat will give you the answer to the rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.44,1:23:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能\NPerhaps.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.92,1:23:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,其实我可以直接指控伯爵夫人\NI could point an easy finger at the, uh, Countess Andrenyi.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.00,1:23:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现她是索尼娅·阿姆斯特朗的妹妹\NI discovered she was Sonia Armstrong's sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.60,1:23:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定  是的\NAre you certain? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.16,1:23:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,可我猜她是无辜的\NI suspect she may perhaps be innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.00,1:23:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但只是猜测\NPerhaps.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.52,1:23:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这趟列车上\NBut so many people have lied to me
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.00,1:23:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有太多人对我撒谎了\Non this train and do not seem to mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.32,1:23:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,包括德贝汉小姐你在内也是如此\NYou yourself did so effortlessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.76,1:23:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我?\NMe?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.96,1:23:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你从没去过美国\NYou told me you had never been to America.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.84,1:23:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你还隐瞒了一个事实\NYou also concealed the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.12,1:23:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,悲剧发生时\Nthat at the time of the tragedy...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.32,1:24:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你就住在阿姆斯特朗家里\Nyou were living in the Armstrong household...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.52,1:24:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,做他们女儿的家庭教师\Nas governess to their daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.00,1:24:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,整件事你很清楚\NAnd you know this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.24,1:24:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我也得过日子\NI have my living to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.28,1:24:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,一个女人牵扯上谋杀案\NA girl detained in connection to a murder case...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.32,1:24:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就没有哪个正经人家敢请我了\Nno decent class family would engage me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.08,1:24:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是你一手策划了雷切特的谋杀案\NMiss Debenham, you planned Ratchett's murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.96,1:24:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你还叫来了伯爵夫人\NAnd then you sent for the countess to witness it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.20,1:24:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,如果她看到他死了\NIf she saw him dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.76,1:24:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识的海伦娜就会回来\Nthe Helena you knew might return.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.44,1:24:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你想等你的室友入睡 可她睡不着\NYou waited for your roommate to sleep, but she did not.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.72,1:24:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,于是你就下药\NYou drugged her.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.80,1:24:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但药力只让她感到了头疼\NBut the barbital only gave her a headache.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.20,1:24:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,列车靠站时 她出门要阿司匹林\NShe begged for an aspirin when the train stopped,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.56,1:24:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,列车员去了站台\Nwhen the conductor was on the station...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.20,1:24:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,周围终于没人了\Nwhen the coast was clear at last...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.36,1:24:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,于是你偷偷溜进了\Nwhen you were allowed to enter
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.48,1:24:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特的房间\NRatchett's compartment, unseen.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.84,1:24:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你爱黛西·阿姆斯特朗 你杀了卡萨蒂\NYou loved Daisy Armstrong. You killed Cassetti.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.08,1:24:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,卡萨蒂禽兽不如\NCassetti was a pig.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.88,1:24:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他死有余辜\NHe deserved to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.28,1:24:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,人不是她杀的\NShe didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.24,1:24:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是我\NI did.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.56,1:24:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,玛丽 快走\NMary, go.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.96,1:25:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我一人做事\NI can't let you take the blame...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.76,1:25:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,一人当\Nfor what I did alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.72,1:25:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,玛丽 求你了 快走\NMary, please, go.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.96,1:25:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗是我最好的朋友\NJohn Armstrong was my best friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.56,1:25:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我的指挥官\Nmy commander.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.20,1:25:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他信任我\NHe believed in me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.72,1:25:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他送我去了医学院 给了我未来\NHe sent me to medical school, gave me a future.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.32,1:25:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,是卡萨蒂害死了他\NCassetti destroyed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.84,1:25:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我心情悲痛 结识了玛丽\NIn grief, I found Mary.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.68,1:25:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我找到了雷切特\NThen I found Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.44,1:25:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我们本想向警方揭发他 正如你之前听到的那样\NOur plan was to reveal him to the police,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.60,1:25:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,可我看到他那张脸\Nthat's what you heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.72,1:25:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\NBut when I saw his face...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.24,1:25:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他连上被告席的资格都没有\NI knew he didn't deserve a trial.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.92,1:25:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你迷晕了麦奎因\NSo, you drugged MacQueen.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.36,1:25:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你调了手表上的时间\NYou changed the time on the watch...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.60,1:25:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这样你就能伪造雷切特的死亡时间了\Nso that you could lie about the time of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.72,1:26:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能让你指控玛丽\NI couldn't let Mary be accused.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.32,1:26:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,还有麦奎因\NOr MacQueen.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.12,1:26:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我的罪孽应该由我一个人来赎\NMy sins are mine to pay for, alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.16,1:26:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个士兵\NI'm a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.96,1:26:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,士兵杀人是为了保护他人\NA soldier kills to protect.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.56,1:26:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在 波洛先生\NAnd now, Mr. Poirot,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.00,1:26:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我不得不保护我自己\NI must protect myself from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.88,1:26:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你还没死\NWhy aren't you dead yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.40,1:26:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,波洛\NPoirot?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.00,1:26:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,先生们 请停下\NGentlemen, stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.72,1:26:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,先生 我们得让所有乘客\NSir, we need to get all the passengers
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.32,1:26:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,回到车上去\Nback on the train.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.04,1:27:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你们先\NYou will retire...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.40,1:27:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,别靠近列车\Naway from the train...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.00,1:27:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,直到我叫你们过来\Nuntil I tell you to return.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.12,1:27:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你们满口谎言\NYou tell your lies...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.72,1:27:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,以为没人会识破\Nand you think no one will know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.68,1:27:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但至少会有两个人知道真相\NBut there are two people who will know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.64,1:27:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,对 两个人\NYes, two people.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.32,1:27:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你们的上帝\NYour God...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.00,1:27:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,还有我赫尔克里·波洛\Nand Hercule Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.16,1:27:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,是时候结束这一切了\NIt is time to solve this case.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.40,1:28:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯诺特医生刚才问为什么我还没死\NDr. Arbuthnot asked me why I was not yet dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.44,1:28:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他当然知道答案\NHe knew, of course, the answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.32,1:28:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,那么近的距离神枪手会射偏吗\NA sharpshooter who does not kill at close range?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.80,1:28:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,刚才那枪不仅没有射偏 相反还很准\NYour shot was not a mistake. It was a surgery.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.64,1:28:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你没杀我是因为你不是杀人犯\NYou could not kill me because you are no killer.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.84,1:28:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都不是杀人犯\NNone of you are killers.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.00,1:28:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,但总得有这么一位凶手\NAnd yet, someone must be.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.40,1:28:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这起案子可以有两种结论 第一种\NThere are two possible solutions to this crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.44,1:28:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,很难 因为它最符合情理\NOne difficult, because it fits with most
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.96,1:28:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,但不是全部真相\Nbut not all of the facts...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.28,1:28:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,而另一个\Nand one more...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.20,1:28:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,更复杂\Ncomplex.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.84,1:28:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,第一个结论\NThe first solution.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.00,1:28:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特有个仇家\NRatchett had enemies.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.88,1:28:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,一个凶残的黑手党 趁医生他们下车时\NA rogue Mafioso steals onto the train at Vinkovci...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.92,1:28:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,在温科夫齐偷溜上了车\Nas MacQueen and Arbuthnot take the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.40,1:29:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,穿着制服 拿着钥匙\NEquipped with a uniform
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.84,1:29:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,捅死了雷切特\Nand a passkey, he stabs Ratchett.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.60,1:29:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,再从哈伯德夫人的包厢逃走\NHe leaves through Mrs. Hubbard's compartment,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.64,1:29:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,然后成功逃脱\Nand makes his escape.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.08,1:29:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不对\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.76,1:29:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不对 这根本说不通\NNo, no, no. It doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.32,1:29:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么要藏起制服\NWhy hide the uniform, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.72,1:29:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,谁迷晕了雷切特\NWho drugs Ratchett?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.48,1:29:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,又是谁刺伤了哈伯德夫人\NOr stabs Mrs. Hubbard?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.96,1:29:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,别胡扯\NDamn it, man!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.80,1:29:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,所以谁是最大的受益者\NSo I ask, who stands to benefit?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.96,1:29:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这起谋杀案的死者是一名杀人犯\NThis crime is the murdering of a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.28,1:29:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这么做或许是为了\NThe benefit is, perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.12,1:29:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在精神上 减轻痛苦\Nto the spirit, an ease of suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.64,1:29:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,为了赶走脑海中\NTo quiet a shouting voice
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.04,1:29:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,令人难以入眠的叫声\Nin the head that prevents sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.64,1:29:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手就在我们之中\NThere is a murderer among us.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.48,1:29:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,所以\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.92,1:29:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的阿巴斯诺特医生\NWe have Dr. Arbuthnot,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.20,1:29:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,作为阿姆斯特朗上校最忠实的朋友\Na dedicated, grateful friend to Colonel Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.96,1:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他遇到了\NHe meets and finds solace
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.40,1:30:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,能带给他一丝安慰的家庭教师\Nin the company of the governess, Mary Debenham...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.36,1:30:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,和黛西亲如母女的玛丽·德贝汉\Nwho is almost like a mother to the little girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.24,1:30:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,她还和索尼娅·阿姆斯特朗的妹妹 走得非常近\NAnd so close to Mrs. Armstrong's young sister,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.16,1:30:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,海伦娜·戈登伯格\NHelena Goldenberg...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.24,1:30:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,她嫁给了一个权贵\Nmarried to a powerful man
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.80,1:30:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,一个暴力而又易怒的男人\Nno stranger to rage and violence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.52,1:30:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我们之中还有黛西的教母\NWe travel also with Daisy's godmother...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.44,1:30:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,而这个人同样也是\Nto whom belongs...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.48,1:30:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在案发现场发现的\Nthe monogrammed handkerchief
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.44,1:30:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,那条绣着字母手帕的主人\Nfound at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.80,1:30:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,上面的H 在俄语的字母表里面\NThe letter "H" in the Russian alphabet,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.92,1:30:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,其实应该读作 N\Nof course, pronounced "N."
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.40,1:30:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,娜塔莉·德拉戈米罗夫\NNatalia Dragomiroff.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.00,1:30:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而她这位对菜肴有着独到品味的女仆\NAnd her devoted maid with a chef's eye?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.80,1:30:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,在这之前是做什么的呢\NWho was she before her current employ?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.32,1:30:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜她是阿姆斯特朗家的厨子\NMight I suggest the Armstrongs' cook?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.44,1:30:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,到这里故事还没有结束\NBut we are not yet done.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.04,1:30:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,照顾黛西的那位保姆\NThe nurse in charge of Daisy...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.00,1:30:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,出于内疚她从此信了教\Nher newfound religious zeal
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.68,1:30:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,因为她照看的孩子\Nborn of guilt at allowing her charge...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.48,1:30:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,被绑走了\Nto be abducted. It was you, was it not...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.60,1:30:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那天雷切特从窗户溜进去时\Nin her room the night when
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.76,1:30:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该就在房里\NRatchett came in through the window?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.96,1:31:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,那天晚餐\NDid you have a glass of wine too many
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.56,1:31:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你是不是多喝了一杯\Nwith your supper that night?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.80,1:31:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,因此你不断责怪自己不够警觉\NHave you blamed yourself ever since...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.72,1:31:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,所以才没能阻止他\Nfor not being alert to stop him?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.48,1:31:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,她是那么纯真 那么善良\NShe knew nothing but kindness...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.40,1:31:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,那么可爱 可是\Nand love, until...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.04,1:31:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,可是\Nuntil I...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.96,1:31:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我就不劳您费心了 先生\NNo need to divine with me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.56,1:31:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我是阿姆斯特朗上校一战时的勤务兵\NI was Colonel Armstrong's batman in the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.84,1:31:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,退伍后 我成了他在纽约的管家\NAnd afterwards, his valet in New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.40,1:31:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他是天底下最高尚的人\NAs fine a man as God ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.32,1:31:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他的司机也会这样说吧\NWould his chauffeur agree?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.52,1:31:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,正是上校的担保 他凭借银行的贷款\NWas it a bank loan, secured by Armstrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.56,1:31:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,建立起了自己的汽车帝国\Nallows him to build his automobile empire?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.40,1:31:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这份恩情永远还不清 还有谁最为可疑\NHe's indebted for life. Who else can we count?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.16,1:31:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这位私家侦探\NWhat of the Pinkerton detective,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.80,1:31:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,当年被指派负责\Nonce a police officer...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.16,1:31:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,阿姆斯特朗案的警官\Nassigned to the Armstrong case?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.56,1:31:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他对某人动了情\NAnd he becomes attached to someone,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.92,1:31:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在当年的案件里 还有一个不为人知的受害者\Nfor there is another, uncelebrated victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.96,1:31:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在那位女仆受到污蔑之前\NYou fell in love with the maid
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.72,1:31:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经爱上了她\Nbefore she was falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.96,1:31:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,当你目睹了正义被人扭曲\NYou quit the police when you witnessed...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.64,1:32:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你选择了辞职\Nthe travesty ofjustice...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.84,1:32:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,当时麦奎因的父亲坚持要逮捕她\Nwhen MacQueen's father insisted on her arrest.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.92,1:32:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,最后她选择了自杀\NWhen she took her own life.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.44,1:32:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不\NNo! No, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.68,1:32:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,苏珊为人非常温柔\NSusanne was so gentle.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.96,1:32:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,而她爱上了我\NAnd she fell for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.88,1:32:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我头发都花白了\NOld and already getting grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.84,1:32:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我劝她找一个更好的 可是\NI told her she could do better...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.00,1:32:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,她就是这样\Nbut there she was...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.12,1:32:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,每次约会都很准时\Non time for every date.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.84,1:32:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\NWhy else is a train...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.08,1:32:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,大冬天列车还会客满 为什么伤口会深浅不一\Nso full in the dead of winter? Why the inconsistent wounds?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.52,1:32:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么会有那么多证物\NWhy the abundance of evidence? Why...?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.24,1:32:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么还有列车员\NWhy the conductor?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.52,1:32:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,阿维尼翁的皮埃尔·米歇尔\NPierre Michel of Avignon...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.16,1:32:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,失去了他的姐姐\Nwho lost his sister...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.04,1:32:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,被诬告的那名女仆\Nthe accused maid...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.72,1:32:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,苏珊·米歇尔\NSusanne Michel.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.00,1:33:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一人 可以说\NOnly one soul can claim to have lost
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.20,1:33:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,比你们中任何人失去的都要多\Nmore than any of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.28,1:33:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜的琳达·雅顿\NThe tragic Linda Arden...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.32,1:33:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,索尼娅的母亲\Nmother of Sonia...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.60,1:33:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,小黛西的外婆\Ngrandmother of Daisy.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.96,1:33:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,早已从舞台隐退\NRetired from the stage...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.72,1:33:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但却献上了最后一场表演\Nbut for one final performance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.24,1:33:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个极其聪明的男人\NYou're an awfully clever man.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.00,1:33:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,一起命案造成了一个生命的逝去\NA murder should have one victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.56,1:33:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,而当雷切特杀死了黛西·阿姆斯特朗的时候\NWhen Ratchett kills Daisy Armstrong...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.76,1:33:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,十几条生命随之破碎 扭曲 终结\Na dozen lives are broken, deformed, ended.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.04,1:33:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要求正义\NThey demand justice!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.32,1:34:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管那么多受伤的灵魂 我们还是得找出\NOf all these wounded souls, we must finally answer...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.92,1:34:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在他们之中 谁是凶手\Nwho among them is a killer?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.08,1:34:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,是谁拿起了刀子 答案就是\NWho takes up the knife? The answer is...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.12,1:34:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,凭一己之力是无法做到的\NNo single one of you could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.88,1:34:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,两个人也不行\NNor any pair.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.96,1:34:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一的可能就是\NIt can only have been done...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.08,1:34:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你们所有人都参与了\Nby all of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.80,1:34:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你们所有人\NTogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.12,1:34:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你们所有人\NTogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.92,1:34:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,突然的雪崩打乱了你们的计划\NEven when the avalanche changes everything...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.12,1:34:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,由于侦探的出现\Nas does the detective, plans must change.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.04,1:34:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,计划必须改变 红色睡袍 还有制服\NThe kimono, the uniform.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.76,1:34:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,出神入化的即兴表演\NA remarkable improvisation,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.08,1:34:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,以及一个知道如何避开要害的医生\Nthe doctor who knows how to wound without killing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.32,1:34:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都扮演着一个角色\NEach has their part to play.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.44,1:34:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,动手\NDo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.28,1:34:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,全是我的计划\NIt was my plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.12,1:34:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,是我找的他们\NI recruited them.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.76,1:34:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我让哈德曼追查卡萨蒂的下落\NI had Hardman track down Cassetti.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.36,1:34:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,让麦奎因去替他工作\NI sent MacQueen to work for him,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.12,1:35:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,接着是马斯特曼\Nand then Masterman.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.28,1:35:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,麦奎因可以安排\NMacQueen could arrange
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.36,1:35:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他在米歇尔当班时出行\Nhe travel on the day that Michel was on duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.12,1:36:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,雷切特先生\NMr. Ratchett?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.68,1:36:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么事\NIt's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.04,1:36:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,好的先生 晚安\NBien, monsieur. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.48,1:36:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一切就这么完成了\NAnd so it is done.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.12,1:37:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,为了无辜的逝者\NFor the death of the innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.76,1:37:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一命偿一命\NA life for a life.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.84,1:37:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,复仇\NRevenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.92,1:37:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,被绞死的应该是我 和他们无关\NNo one should hang for this but me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.08,1:37:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,是我一手策划的\NIt was my plan!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.56,1:37:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉警察是我一个人干的\NTell the police it was me, alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.84,1:37:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,反正我早已经没有活下去的意义了\NThere's no life left in me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.00,1:37:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他们现在还有机会\NThey have a chance now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.16,1:37:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,海伦娜 我祈祷\NHelena, I pray...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.60,1:37:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,她应该还有机会\Nhas a chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.80,1:37:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他们可以\NThey can...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.60,1:37:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,继续生活\Ngo live...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.92,1:37:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在某个地方\Nfind some joy...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.12,1:37:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,找到快乐\Nsomewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.60,1:37:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,让我来结束这一切\NLet it end with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.28,1:37:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他们不是杀人犯\NThey're not killers.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.80,1:37:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他们都是好人\NThey're good people.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.28,1:37:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他们可以继续做好人\NThey can be good again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.52,1:38:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,凡事要么是对的 要么是错的\NThere was right, there was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.44,1:38:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,现在多了你们\NNow there is you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.36,1:38:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我无法做出判断\NI cannot judge this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.80,1:38:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,由你们来决定\NYou must decide.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.28,1:38:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们想逃避\NYou wish to go free
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.36,1:38:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你们所犯下的罪行\Nwithout punishment for your crime...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.64,1:38:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,那你们就得多杀一个人\Nthen you must only commit one more.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.68,1:38:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会阻止你们\NI will not stop you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.48,1:38:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能让他们杀了你\NYou can't let them kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.64,1:38:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你们把我的尸体扔进河里\NYou give my body to the lake,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.04,1:38:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这样就能清白的走出这个站台\Nand you walk away innocent at the station.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.68,1:38:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你们得封我的口\NYou must silence me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.96,1:38:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,布克可以说谎\NBouc can lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.32,1:38:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,而我做不到\NI cannot.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.12,1:38:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,动手啊 谁都可以\NDo it! One of you!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.24,1:38:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,别乱来\NDon't.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.20,1:38:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我的心早就跟着黛西一起死了\NI already died with Daisy.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.32,1:39:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.56,1:39:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你的职责是寻求正义\NYou said your role was to find justice.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.52,1:39:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在这儿什么才是正义\NWhat is justice here?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.80,1:39:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,有时光靠法律是远远不够的\NSometimes, the law of man is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.12,1:40:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,良知又该置于何处\NWhere does conscience lie?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.76,1:40:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,和黛西一起埋葬了\NBuried with Daisy.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.44,1:42:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的阿姆斯特朗上校\NMy dear Colonel Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.92,1:42:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,终于 我可以给你回信了\NFinally, I can answer your letter...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.24,1:42:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,至于我脑海中的想法\Nat least with the thoughts in my head
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.40,1:42:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我内心的感受\Nand the feeling in my heart...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.96,1:42:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在某个地方 你一定听得到\Nthat somewhere, you can hear me.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.44,1:42:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在已经揭开了\NI have now discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.96,1:42:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,案件的真相\Nthe truth of the case, and it is...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.68,1:42:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,结果让人十分不安\Nprofoundly disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.32,1:43:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我见识了人性的破碎\NI have seen the fracture of the human soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.28,1:43:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那么多不幸的人生 那么多的痛苦和愤怒\NSo many broken lives, so much pain and anger...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.48,1:43:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,被心底深处的那份悲痛所支配着\Ngiving way to the poison of deep grief...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.60,1:43:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,直到一起罪行引发了连锁反应\Nuntil one crime became many.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.64,1:43:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直都愿意相信\NI have always wanted to believe
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.80,1:43:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,人类是理性并且文明的\Nthat man is rational and civilized.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.68,1:43:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我的存在正是基于这份信念\NMy very existence depends upon this hope...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.28,1:43:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,加上我看事物独到的方法 以及我的那点脑细胞\Nupon order and method and the little gray cells.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.72,1:43:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在或许\NBut now, perhaps, I am asked...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.48,1:43:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要转变一下\Nto listen, instead...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.48,1:43:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,听从我的心声\Nto my heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.68,1:43:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们\NLadies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.84,1:43:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,通过这起案子我意识到 正义的天平\NI have understood in this case that the scales of justice...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.24,1:43:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,未必能永远保持平衡\Ncannot always be evenly weighed.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.16,1:44:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,而这也让我头一次学会了\NAnd I must learn, for once...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.72,1:44:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,去接受这个世界的不平衡\Nto live with the imbalance.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.52,1:44:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,车上没有杀人犯\NThere are no killers here.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.04,1:44:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,只有值得好好活下去的人\NOnly people who deserve a chance to heal.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.40,1:44:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,警方已经接受了\NThe police have accepted
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.84,1:44:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我的第一种结论\Nmy first solution to the crime...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.40,1:44:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,凶手单独作案并且成功逃逸\Nthe lone assassin who made his escape.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.32,1:44:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在要下车去办结案手续了\NI will leave the train here to conclude formalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.16,1:44:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都可以离开了\NYou are all free to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.52,1:44:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,希望你们能就此获得安宁\NAnd may you find your peace with this.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.80,1:44:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,希望我们都能如此\NMay we all.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.20,1:44:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,您好\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.84,1:44:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我在找一位叫波洛的先生\NI'm looking for a Mr. Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.52,1:44:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,有紧急事件要找他\NHe's needed on a very urgent matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.36,1:45:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他正在休假\NAh. He is on holiday.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.84,1:45:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,又是卡斯纳的案子\NThe, uh, Kassner case again?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.04,1:45:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,不 先生 更糟糕\NNo, sir, far worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.68,1:45:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须得马上带他去埃及\NI have to take him to Egypt straight away.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.72,1:45:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,那儿发生了一起谋杀案 在该死的尼罗河上\NThere's been a murder, sir, right on the bloody Nile.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.24,1:45:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,您就是那位侦探吗\NAre you the detective?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.60,1:45:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.92,1:45:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是那个侦探\NI am the detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.72,1:45:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以把领带摆正吗\NCould you please straighten your tie?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.92,1:45:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,一会儿车上见\NI will see you at the car.

